html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 02:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 02:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/aegon-benoemt-allegra-van-hovell-patrizi-als-chief-risk-officer-553126401.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/aegon-benoemt-allegra-van-hovell-patrizi-als-chief-risk-officer-553126401.html\"],\"description\":\"DEN HAAG, Nederland, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nMet ingang van 1 januari 2016 benoemt Aegon Allegra van H&#246;vell-Patrizi (41, Italiaans) tot Chief Risk Officer en lid van de Management Board van Aegon. Zij wordt wereldwijd verantwoordelijk voor risicobeheer, actuariaat en Aegon\'s interne \",\"content\":\"DEN HAAG, Nederland, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nMet ingang van 1 januari 2016 benoemt Aegon Allegra van H&#246;vell-Patrizi (41, Italiaans) tot Chief Risk Officer en lid van de Management Board van Aegon. Zij wordt wereldwijd verantwoordelijk voor risicobeheer, actuariaat en Aegon\'s interne \",\"title\":\"Aegon benoemt Allegra van Hövell-Patrizi als Chief Risk Officer\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"DEN HAAG, Nederland, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\",\"Tom Grondin (46, Canadees) wordt Chief Financial Officer van Aegon Azië en treedt daarmee terug uit de Management Board van Aegon. Als CFO wordt hij in Azië verantwoordelijk voor financiën en het managen van alle activiteiten die de balans beïnvloeden. Tom Grondin was sinds 2003 Chief Risk Officer bij Aegon en sinds 2013 lid van de Management Board.\",\"\\\"Ik wil Tom bedanken voor zijn grote bijdrage aan het opbouwen van het risicobeheer binnen Aegon. We zijn blij met zijn overstap, zodat hij ons in Azië kan helpen met de verdere groei van onze succesvolle business daar,\\\" zegt CEO Alex Wynaendts. \\\"Ik ben verheugd dat Allegra bij ons als Chief Risk Officer aan boord komt. Ze brengt een schat aan ervaring en expertise mee om deze belangrijke positie verder in te vullen. Ze zal een centrale rol spelen in het versterken en optimaliseren van ons bedrijf.\\\"\",\"De benoeming van mevrouw van Hövell-Patrizi is afhankelijk van goedkeuring door DNB.\",\"Voor het officiële Engelstalige persbericht verwijzen wij naar de corporate website aegon.com.\",\"Media relations\\nDebora de Laaf\\n+31-(0)70-344-8730\\ngcc@aegon.com\\n\\n\",\"Investor relations\\nWillem van den Berg\\n+31-(0)70-344-8405\\nir@aegon.com\\n\\n\",\"    PRN NLD\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 07:09:03','2015-11-24 07:09:03',NULL),(10635,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/accedian-signs-worldwide-framework-agreement-to-globally-assure-transport-network-quality-at-telefonica-553126111.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 02:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 02:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/accedian-signs-worldwide-framework-agreement-to-globally-assure-transport-network-quality-at-telefonica-553126111.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/accedian-signs-worldwide-framework-agreement-to-globally-assure-transport-network-quality-at-telefonica-553126111.html\"],\"description\":\"Telef&#243;nica advances customer experience by optimizing end-to-end network performance to ensure exceptional quality of service and reliability.\\n\\n\\n\\nMADRID, Spain, Nov. 24, 2015 /CNW/ -&#160;Accedian Networks, the global leader in end-to-end network performance assurance, today announced that Tele\",\"content\":\"Telef&#243;nica advances customer experience by optimizing end-to-end network performance to ensure exceptional quality of service and reliability.\\n\\n\\n\\nMADRID, Spain, Nov. 24, 2015 /CNW/ -&#160;Accedian Networks, the global leader in end-to-end network performance assurance, today announced that Tele\",\"title\":\"Accedian Signs Worldwide Framework Agreement to Globally Assure Transport Network Quality at Telefónica\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"\",\"MADRID, Spain, Nov. 24, 2015 /CNW/ - Accedian Networks, the global leader in end-to-end network performance assurance, today announced that Telefónica (NYSE:   TEF) has selected Accedian\'s network performance assurance to deliver a new level of customer experience to their mobile subscribers, business and residential customers across Telefónica\'s global footprint. Accedian will provide ubiquitous, real-time network performance visibility to deliver the best possible quality of service (QoS) and reliability, building on solutions used by 18 of the world\'s top 20 mobile operators, and supported by more than 35 international patents.\",\"The Accedian solution unifies QoS visibility over Telefónica\'s multi-vendor metro and backhaul networks using a standards-based approach. It assures transport network performance for a full range of LTE applications including mobile broadband, VoLTE, video streaming, voice and text messaging, internet of things (IoT) connectivity, and value-added roaming services for partner carriers. \",\"\\\"Thanks to this partnership with Accedian, Telefónica´s customers will be able to take advantage of the improvement in end-to-end network performance assurance. We feel confident of our ability to deliver the highest possible levels of quality of experience (QoE) at all locations we serve, which is translated into transformative opportunities for our customers. We view Accedian as a key partner in this strategic project,\\\" stated Enrique Blanco, Telefónica Global CTO.\",\"\\\"Telefónica\'s impressive global footprint and leadership is underscored by its transformative, open, agile, and dependable network. Accedian is pleased to have the opportunity to help Telefónica further its position as the connectivity of partner of choice by ensuring they have the real-time visibility required to optimize network control, and deliver a differentiated performance experience to their subscribers,\\\" stated Accedian Founder, President, and CEO, Patrick Ostiguy.\",\"About AccedianAccedian delivers exceptional end-to-end network performance visibility, for control over the best possible user experience. Providing the most complete, current view of network health, Accedian dramatically improves visibility with actionable insights for peak reliability and quality of service (QoS). Accedian enables control over increasingly complex networks to increase agility, and reduce cost. Most importantly, through a fully optimized and performance assured network, Accedian proactively ensures maximum uptime and for peak quality of experience (QoE). Since 2005, Accedian has assured hundreds of thousands of networks and services globally, turning performance into a key competitive differentiator. For more information, visit Accedian.com. Twitter: @Accedian\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 07:09:05','2015-11-24 07:09:05',NULL),(10636,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/aegon-appoints-allegra-van-hovell-patrizi-as-chief-risk-officer-553126131.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 02:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 02:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/aegon-appoints-allegra-van-hovell-patrizi-as-chief-risk-officer-553126131.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/aegon-appoints-allegra-van-hovell-patrizi-as-chief-risk-officer-553126131.html\"],\"description\":\"THE HAGUE, the Netherlands, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nAegon today announces the appointment of Allegra van H&#246;vell-Patrizi (41, Italian) as Chief Risk Officer and member of the Management Board, effective as of January 1, 2016. Her responsibilities will include managing Aegon\'s Risk and\",\"content\":\"THE HAGUE, the Netherlands, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nAegon today announces the appointment of Allegra van H&#246;vell-Patrizi (41, Italian) as Chief Risk Officer and member of the Management Board, effective as of January 1, 2016. Her responsibilities will include managing Aegon\'s Risk and\",\"title\":\"Aegon Appoints Allegra van Hövell-Patrizi as Chief Risk Officer\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"THE HAGUE, the Netherlands, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\",\"Aegon today announces the appointment of Allegra van Hövell-Patrizi (41, Italian) as Chief Risk Officer and member of the Management Board, effective as of January 1, 2016. Her responsibilities will include managing Aegon\'s Risk and Actuarial functions, together with overseeing the Group\'s Risk Structuring &amp; Transfer capabilities. Ms. van Hövell-Patrizi joins Aegon from Prudential plc where she was Group Risk Director, having previously held various risk management positions.\",\"Tom Grondin (46, Canadian) will become Chief Financial Officer for Aegon\'s operations in Asia and will step down from Aegon\'s Management Board. As CFO for the region, he will be responsible for finance and overall balance sheet management activities. Mr. Grondin has been Aegon\'s Chief Risk Officer since 2003 and on Aegon\'s Management Board since 2013.\",\"\\\"I want to thank Tom for his immense contribution in building up Aegon\'s risk management function. We are pleased that he will be in a key position to help us continue the successful growth of our Asian business,\\\" said CEO Alex Wynaendts. \\\"I\'m also delighted that Allegra will be joining us as Chief Risk Officer. She brings a wealth of highly relevant experience and expertise to this key leadership position, and will play a central role as Aegon continues to enhance its business.\\\"\",\"Ms. van Hövell-Patrizi\'s appointment is subject to regulatory approval.\",\"Media relations\\nDebora de Laaf\\n+31-(0)-70-344-8730\\ngcc@aegon.com\\n\\n\",\"Investor relations\\nWillem van den Berg\\n+31-(0)-70-344-8405\\nir@aegon.com\\n\\n\",\"    PRN NLD\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11