CFO Your New BFF\\\" on December 2nd, 2015 from 2:00pm - 3:00pm EST/EDT. ClearSlide\'s VP of Marketing &amp; Business Development Michael \",\"content\":\"SAN FRANCISCO, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- ClearSlide, the leading platform for sales, marketing and customer success, will hold an AA-ISP webinar titled \\\"Make the CFO Your New BFF\\\" on December 2nd, 2015 from 2:00pm - 3:00pm EST/EDT. ClearSlide\'s VP of Marketing &amp; Business Development Michael \",\"title\":\"ClearSlide Announces AA-ISP Webinar For Sales Leaders Looking To Leverage Data For Forecast Accuracy\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"SAN FRANCISCO, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- ClearSlide, the leading platform for sales, marketing and customer success, will hold an AA-ISP webinar titled \\\"Make the CFO Your New BFF\\\" on December 2nd, 2015 from 2:00pm - 3:00pm EST/EDT. ClearSlide\'s VP of Marketing &amp; Business Development Michael Shultz and VP of Product Raj Gossain will lead the session, which will teach sales leaders how to reduce forecast inaccuracy and leverage data to coach their teams to success.\",\"The late baseball legend Yogi Berra once said, \\\"It\'s tough to make predictions, especially about the future.\\\" And yet, sales leaders are expected to make performance predictions every quarter, even though research shows that 50 percent of all forecasted deals slip. Because of this lack of precision, CFOs are forced to adjust forecasts based on gut instinct and past results. This makes it difficult to have confidence in revenue forecasts or to give earnings guidance. New predictive forecasting tools can be transformative for sales leaders, but the key is looking at actual customer engagement.\",\"In this compelling session, Schultz and Gossain will discuss how Predictive Insights can be leveraged to gain better confidence in your pipeline, identify deals at risk or ones that can be moved forward, and have the engagement data to coach more effectively - making the CFO your new best friend.\",\"Schultz leads Marketing and Business Development for ClearSlide. Prior to ClearSlide, he served as VP of Strategic Alliances at DocuSign, where he built out and managed the company\'s key partnerships and programs over three years of rapid growth. Schultz spent nearly eight years with Microsoft Corporation in various SaaS product management and marketing roles following the acquisition of PlaceWare web conferencing. He has also held senior positions with other venture-backed and publicly traded companies, and previously worked as a strategy consultant at Andersen Consulting (now Accenture). Schultz earned an MBA from the Tuck School at Dartmouth and a BA in English from Tufts University.\",\"Gossain drives Product and User Experience strategy and execution at ClearSlide. Prior to joining ClearSlide, he was VP &amp; GM for new cloud &amp; mobile collaboration apps at Cisco Systems where he ran the Project Squared team. Prior to that he was VP Products for Cisco WebEx. He has an 18 year career in general management, product management and product marketing for global technology companies including Cisco WebEx, Yahoo!, Netscape &amp; AOL. Gossain earned his MBA from Harvard Business School and a BS in Electrical Engineering &amp; Computer Science from the University of California, Berkeley.\",\"Together, these marketing and sales experts will arm sales leaders with the information and tools they need to set and meet realistic goals, leading to greater sales effectiveness and efficiency overall. \",\"What: AA-ISP webinar, \\\"Make the CFO Your New BFF\\\"\",\"Who: Michael Schultz, VP of Marketing &amp; Business Development, ClearSlide; Raj Gossain, VP of Product, ClearSlide \",\"When: Wednesday, December 2nd from 2:00pm - 3:00pm EST/EDT\",\"Where: Register to Join\",\"To learn more about ClearSlide, visit www.clearslide.com\",\"About ClearSlide: ClearSlide is the Platform for Sales, Marketing and Customer Success that powers valuable, genuine business conversations and enables organizations to achieve better business outcomes. ClearSlide improves customer communications (phone, email, face-to-face) by providing real-time visibility and analytics for sales and marketing leaders. As a result, customers achieve higher seller productivity, increased sales management effectiveness and stronger customer-facing messaging. Founded in 2009 and headquartered in San Francisco, ClearSlide serves thousands of customers, including Rackspace, Thomson Reuters, Comcast, SurveyMonkey, LinkedIn, and more.\",\"The ClearSlide platform gives sales and marketing leaders insight into the real-time activity of their teams and provides deep analytics about the types of content that ultimately is most impactful with customers. For sales professionals, ClearSlide allows for easy communication with customers and prospects, whether online or in-person, using ClearSlide\'s web-based or mobile applications. \",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 13:03:13','2015-11-24 13:03:13',NULL),(10952,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/partnership-with-native-americans-joins-newmans-own-foundation-for-givingtuesday-challenge-300183774.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 07:45:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 07:45:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/partnership-with-native-americans-joins-newmans-own-foundation-for-givingtuesday-challenge-300183774.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/partnership-with-native-americans-joins-newmans-own-foundation-for-givingtuesday-challenge-300183774.html\"],\"description\":\"ADDISON, Texas, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Partnership With Native Americans (PWNA) encourages everyone to give back this season as a participant in the Newman\'s Own Foundation Challenge for #GivingTuesday, a global day of giving that harnesses the collective power of individuals, communitie\",\"content\":\"ADDISON, Texas, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Partnership With Native Americans (PWNA) encourages everyone to give back this season as a participant in the Newman\'s Own Foundation Challenge for #GivingTuesday, a global day of giving that harnesses the collective power of individuals, communitie\",\"title\":\"Partnership With Native Americans Joins Newman\'s Own Foundation For #GivingTuesday Challenge\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"ADDISON, Texas, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Partnership With Native Americans (PWNA) encourages everyone to give back this season as a participant in the Newman\'s Own Foundation Challenge for #GivingTuesday, a global day of giving that harnesses the collective power of individuals, communities and organizations to promote philanthropy and generosity around the world. \",\"PWNA can earn up to $10,000 in matching funds for donations made between Nov. 24 and Dec. 1, as part of the Newman\'s Own Foundation Challenge. \",\"Funds raised through the Newman\'s Own Foundation Challenge will be put toward PWNA\'s food and water initiatives, supplying food boxes for pantries, serving individual families in need and preparing meals for Native American communities living in poverty or \\\"food deserts.\\\" \",\"\\\"PWNA is grateful to have been selected by Newman\'s Own Foundation,\\\" said PWNA President and CEO Robbi Rice Dietrich. \\\"These potential funds are critical for us to carry out our mission of championing hope for the 60 remote, isolated and impoverished reservations we serve, and improving food security and quality of life for the Native Americans living there.\\\"\",\"PWNA provides immediate relief to Native American communities through goods and services delivered year round for nutrition, health, education, animal welfare and emergency relief. PWNA also supports long-term solutions such as scholarships, training for grassroots leaders and community investment projects to help end the cycle of poverty.  \",\"Taking place on Dec. 1, #GivingTuesday is held annually on the first Tuesday following Thanksgiving, Black Friday, and Cyber Monday to kick-off the holiday giving season. The day is designed to inspire people to collaborate on improving their local communities and to give back in impactful ways to those charities and causes they support. \",\"Donations for the Newman\'s Own Foundation Challenge will be hosted on CrowdRise, an online crowd fundraising platform for nonprofits. PWNA is one of 24 organizations selected to participate this year by Newman\'s Own Foundation, the independent foundation created by late actor and philanthropist, Paul Newman. \",\"To help achieve PWNA\'s challenge goal, please visit www.crowdrise.com/pwna4hope and make a donation between Nov. 24 and Dec. 1. \",\"About Partnership With Native Americans  Partnership With Native Americans (PWNA) is a nonprofit organization committed to championing hope for a brighter future for Native Americans living on remote, isolated and often impoverished reservations. The organization collaborates with its reservation partners to provide immediate relief and support long-term solutions for strong, self-sufficient Native American communities. Established in 1990, PWNA works through its grassroots partnerships and distribution network to improve the lives of 250,000 Native Americans each year. For more information, visit www.nativepartnership.org.\",\"MEDIA CONTACT\",\"Elizabeth Zwerin  623-201-5559  pwna@allisonpr.com\",\"Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20150729/248804LOGO\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 13:03:15','2015-11-24 13:03:15',NULL),(10953,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/elray-gaming----q3-revenues-top-1-million-dollars-300183862.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 07:52:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 07:52:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/elray-gamin