r. Gary Barbera proudly will be on hand to assist in the distribution of turkeys to over 100 families in Strawberry Mansion and surrounding communities.\",\"Contact Tyrone Williams, Community Liaison at 215-235-7505 Ext. 203 or email at Ty0726@msn.com. \",\"Contact Information: \",\"Strawberry Mansion Neighborhood Action Center, Inc.2829 W. Diamond StreetPhiladelphia, PA 19121OFFICE:  (215) 235-7505FAX: (215) 235-3122  \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Details on turkey donations.\"}]}','2015-11-24 16:12:49','2015-11-24 16:12:49',NULL),(11332,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/launch-of-new-mary-square-philanthropic-program-creates-world-wide-impact-300183897.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/launch-of-new-mary-square-philanthropic-program-creates-world-wide-impact-300183897.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/launch-of-new-mary-square-philanthropic-program-creates-world-wide-impact-300183897.html\"],\"description\":\"CARY, N.C., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Mary Square, a gift company specializing in unique, affordable and trendy products, is making a world-wide impact with the launch of its new Five &amp; Two program, a philanthropic initiative that provides resources to people in need through its new cor\",\"content\":\"CARY, N.C., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Mary Square, a gift company specializing in unique, affordable and trendy products, is making a world-wide impact with the launch of its new Five &amp; Two program, a philanthropic initiative that provides resources to people in need through its new cor\",\"title\":\"Launch of New Mary Square Philanthropic Program Creates World-Wide Impact\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"CARY, N.C., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Mary Square, a gift company specializing in unique, affordable and trendy products, is making a world-wide impact with the launch of its new Five &amp; Two program, a philanthropic initiative that provides resources to people in need through its new corporate partnership with World Help. \",\"Mary Square\'s Five &amp; Two program comprises four initiatives to bring hope and healing to impoverished people around the globe. They include:\",\"\\\"Our Five &amp; Two program is an initiative we\'ve dreamed about since the company formed in 2011. Our partnership with World Help turns a Five &amp; Two dream into reality by providing life-saving resources to communities around the world,\\\" said Kelly Shiley, chief executive officer of Mary Square. \\\"Our desire is to see Mary Square retail and wholesale customers gift with purpose and make a long-term impact in lives of those less fortunate.\\\"\",\"The Five &amp; Two program is named after Jesus\'s parable of multiplying five loaves of bread and two fish to feed thousands. Similarly, Mary Square\'s goal is to invest in people, and allow that investment to multiply. \",\"\\\"We\'re excited to welcome Mary Square as a World Help corporate partner,\\\" said Noel Yeatts, vice president of World Help. \\\"The Five &amp; Two program showcases a wonderful style of servant leadership, and we are looking forward to increased opportunities to serve the physical and spiritual needs of people in underprivileged communities around the world.\\\"\",\"Mary Square is in the process of setting 2016 donation goals for its Five &amp; Two program and plans to share progress regularly via www.MarySquare.com. \",\"About Mary Square  Mary Square is a women-owned, faith-based gift company making a positive impact in the world through its innovative business initiative, Five &amp; Two. The company, headquartered in North Carolina, was established in 2011 and specializes in production and sales of unique, affordable and trendy gift products that inspire customers to make each purchase more than a gift. \",\"Through its Five &amp; Two program, the company partners with World Help to provide clean water to citizens of third-world countries. Through its philanthropic program, Mary Square\'s goal is to inspire, equip and encourage customers and consumers to live passionately and gift with purpose, knowing that each purchase makes a difference. \",\"From drinkware to stationery and personal accessories, Mary Square is a premier supplier to independent gift shops as well as national accounts such as LifeWay® Christian Stores, Books-A-Million® and Family Christian® Stores. Additionally, Mary Square\'s e-commerce business sells direct to consumer at www.MarySquare.com.  \",\"Follow Mary Square on Twitter, Facebook, Instagram and Pinterest.\",\"About World Help  World Help is a faith-based humanitarian organization that exists to serve the physical and spiritual needs of people in impoverished communities around the world.\",\"World Help provides strategic aid and relief in crisis and empowers community development through sustainable, holistic projects designed to promote growth without fostering dependency. Within these communities, World Help works to support spiritual development and enrichment. By joining with trusted indigenous partners the seeds of transformation are planted, while enabling the Gospel to be shared. \",\"World Help\'s financial foundation is built on the commitment to total transparency in reporting and accountability. The organization continually seeks to clearly and accurately demonstrate how it impacts millions with help for today and hope for tomorrow.\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 16:22:45','2015-11-24 16:22:45',NULL),(11333,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/online-mortgage-platform-lenda-raises-2-million-from-lakestar-rubicon-ventures-and-500-startups-300183836.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/online-mortgage-platform-lenda-raises-2-million-from-lakestar-rubicon-ventures-and-500-startups-300183836.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/online-mortgage-platform-lenda-raises-2-million-from-lakestar-rubicon-ventures-and-500-startups-300183836.html\"],\"description\":\"SAN FRANCISCO, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Lenda, the first platform that allows homeowners to refinance their mortgage completely online, today announced the close of $2 million in seed funding led by Lakestar and existing investors including Rubicon Ventures and 500 Startups. \\n\\nSince gradua\",\"content\":\"SAN FRANCISCO, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Lenda, the first platform that allows homeowners to refinance their mortgage completely online, today announced the close of $2 million in seed funding led by Lakestar and existing investors including Rubicon Ventures and 500 Startups. \\n\\nSince gradua\",\"title\":\"Online Mortgage Platform Lenda Raises $2 Million from Lakestar, Rubicon Ventures and 500 Startups\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"SAN FRANCISCO, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Lenda, the first platform that allows homeowners to refinance their mortgage completely online, today announced the close of $2 million in seed funding led by Lakestar and existing investors including Rubicon Ventures and 500 Startups. \",\"Since graduating tech accelerator 500 Startups in summer 2014, Lenda has grown 20 percent month over month to surpass $60 million in loans processed for homeowners in California, Washington and Oregon, with additional states launching early next year. Lenda\'s software enables homeowners to transparently compare loan options, receive a free credit report, securely upload documentation, and check loan status in real time. This reduces the traditional time to close from 2 months to 2.5 weeks, saving an average of $20,000 in fees per borrower.  \",\"\\\"Despite the exponential growth of online lending products and services in the U.S., the mortgage industry has been one of the slowest to adapt to consumer demands for easier, faster and more transparent experiences,\\\" said Jason van den Brand, Co-Founder and CEO of Lenda. \\\"Homeowners can complete an entire mortgage application within 45 minutes from their computer, 24/7, and have their loan funded in under three weeks while saving tens of thousands of dollars.\\\"  \",\"By bringing the entire process online, Lenda has the ability to close loans nearly three times faster -- and is saving consumers between .125 to .25 percent less on interest and APR when compared to the mortgage interest and fees from legacy banks. The company\'s platform, which educates its users throughout the entire process, also has licensed representatives available for homeowners who prefer to have any questions answered by live chat, email, or phone. Looking at total savings, Lenda\'s clients have collectively saved over $450,000 in fees and over $3M in interest over the lives of their loans.\",\"\\\"After looking at over 50 real estate technology companies worldwide, Lenda is now our third investment in the space. We love their product and customer-first approach and their 20 percent monthly rate of growth is exceptional for such a young company,\\\" said Manu Gupta, General Partner at Lakestar. \",\"Lenda was co-founded by CEO, Jason van den Brand and CTO, Elijah Murray.  Jason has spent 11 years in the mortgage industry and previously founded two companies related to the sector. \",\"For more information on Lenda, visit www.lenda.com  \",\"About LendaLenda is a first-of-its-kind platform that allows homeowners to complete their home loan online from start to finish. The software enables homeowners to compare loan options, complete their application, securely manage documents, and keep track of their loan\'s status. Customers claim that the user-friendly online experience helps save time and money while providing for a productive, pleasant mortgage experience.  For more information about Lenda, visit www.lenda.com.             \",\"About Lakestar Lakestar makes early and growth-stage investments in disruptive, technology-enabled businesses predominantly in Europe and the United States, which are driven by exceptional entrepreneurs. Lakestar and its general partners have recently invested in SoFi, Cadre, Symphony, Taulia, Algomi, GoEuro, Maker Studios, and Harry\'s Shaving. Historical investments include Facebook, Spotify, Skype, AirBnB, Oscar Health, Klarna, and King.com. The Lakestar team is on the ground in New York, London, Berlin, and Zurich.\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 16:22:47','2015-11-24 16:22:47',NULL),(11334,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/new-hampshire-department-of-revenue-administration-issues-technical-information-release-on-amnesty-300183967.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:12:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:12:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/new-hampshire-department-of-revenue-administration-issues-technical-information-release-on-amnesty-300183967.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/new-hampshire-department-of-revenue-administration-issues-technical-information-release-on-amnesty-300183967.html\"],\"description\":\"DALLAS, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;The New Hampshire Department of Revenue Administration issued a technical information release regarding its upcoming amnesty program (\\\"Program\\\"). Amnesty is scheduled to run from December 1, 2015 through February 15, 2016. Taxpayers participating in amnesty\",\"content\":\"DALLAS, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;The New Hampshire Department of Revenue Administration issued a technical information release regarding its upcoming amnesty program (\\\"Program\\\"). Amnesty is scheduled to run from December 1, 2015 through February 15, 2016. Taxpayers participating in amnesty\",\"title\":\"New Hampshire Department of Revenue Administration Issues Technical Information Release on Amnesty\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"DALLAS, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The New Hampshire Department of Revenue Administration issued a technical information release regarding its upcoming amnesty program (\\\"Program\\\"). Amnesty is scheduled to run from December 1, 2015 through February 15, 2016. Taxpayers participating in amnesty will have a one-time opportunity to receive a waiver of all penalties and one-half interest on outstanding taxes, provided they pay the tax due along with one-half of the applicable annual interest that accrued since the tax was due. Taxes qualifying under the Program include: \",\"See Technical Information Release 2015-006, New Hampshire Department of Revenue Administration, November 17, 2015 for further information.\",\"About Ryan\",\"Ryan is an award-winning global tax services firm, with the largest indirect and property tax practices in North America and the seventh largest corporate tax practice in the United States. With global headquarters in Dallas, Texas, the Firm provides a comprehensive range of state, local, federal, and international tax advisory and consulting services on a multi-jurisdictional basis, including audit defense, tax recovery, credits and incentives, tax process improvement and automation, tax appeals, tax compliance, and strategic planning. Ryan is a three-time recipient of the International Service Excellence Award from the Customer Service Institute of America (CSIA) for its commitment to world-class client service. Empowered by the dynamic myRyan work environment, which is widely recognized as the most innovative in the tax services industry, Ryan\'s multi-disciplinary team of more than 2,100 professionals and associates serves over 12,000 clients in more than 40 countries, including many of the world\'s most prominent Global 5000 companies. More information about Ryan can be found at ryan.com.\",\"TECHNICAL INFORMATION CONTACTS:\",\"Michael MartensPrincipalRyan857.362.7522michael.martens@ryan.com\",\"Jeremiah T. LynchPrincipalRyan212.871.3901jeremiah.lynch@ryan.com\",\"Available Topic Expert(s): For information on the listed expert(s), click appropriate link.Jerry LynchProfNet - https://profnet.prnewswire.com/Subscriber/ExpertProfile.aspx?ei=113520\",\"Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20140716/127737\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 16:22:56','2015-11-24 16:22:56',NULL),(11335,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/chatgame-avatars---a-new-blast-in-video-calling-technology-300183886.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/chatgame-avatars---a-new-blast-in-video-calling-technology-300183886.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/chatgame-avatars---a-new-blast-in-video-calling-technology-300183886.html\"],\"description\":\"SUNNYVALE, Calif., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- ChatGame, Inc. recently reached a major breakthrough. Since the launch of&#160;its first&#160;version in August 2014, ChatGame has covered over 195 countries and was ranked in the Top 10 in&#160;more than 20 countries. \\n\\n\\nWhat makes it different from \",\"content\":\"SUNNYVALE, Calif., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- ChatGame, Inc. recently reached a major breakthrough. Since the launch of&#160;its first&#160;version in August 2014, ChatGame has covered over 195 countries and was ranked in the Top 10 in&#160;more than 20 countries. \\n\\n\\nWhat makes it different from \",\"title\":\"ChatGame Avatars - A New Blast in Video Calling Technology\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"SUNNYVALE, Calif., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- ChatGame, Inc. recently reached a major breakthrough. Since the launch of its first version in August 2014, ChatGame has covered over 195 countries and was ranked in the Top 10 in more than 20 countries. \",\"What makes it different from other video calling applications like Skype and Viber? \",\"ChatGame encompasses many features, including avatars and the beautification features. In addition, ChatGame Add Friends screen makes it easy to add and invite friends. ChatGame lets you use a cool, and pretty adorable version of yourself. \",\"\\\"We\'re trying to make communication more interesting and full with love and help people to have a better communication,\\\" said Bruce Yu, Co-Founder. \\\"Nowadays, a lot of communication tools we have still couldn\'t bridge the distance between people. It\'s not easy to show people\'s feelings in their daily conversations through texting. Using video calls is the best way to get closer to the people you love. Although people know making a video call is the best way to let their feelings show, yet many people don\'t prefer that because they feel less confident and insecure. We are trying to give them a solution, change the way of video calling, make it more enjoyable and less pressure, more interesting, natural and give users the confidence they need. Helping people to see their loved ones and express their love in the most beautiful way.\\\" \",\"Features:\",\"ChatGame is a mobile application that allows you to make phone calls, HD video calls and send text messages to all other ChatGame users for free. It is available for iOS and Androids so far, and requires a 3G or Wi-Fi connection to use. ChatGame has just updated its last mobile app, and in the updated version i.e. 3.0.63, there are various and unique features, like new and interactive user interface, numerous videos avatars and fun backgrounds that you can switch freely. The updated version is more avatar-focused, which adds flair to chatting and makes it more fun! The video call takes less from your Internet data, and it\'s almost equal to the voice call. You can start your video call instantly from your recent contact list. It\'s simple, fast and easy with ChatGame. You can also make new friends and reconnect with your old friends by inviting your friends from other social media apps through ChatGame. \",\"Seemingly wherever you go on the net these days, you need an avatar to enhance the dimensions of your personality and your sense of humor. Sometimes you don\'t want to share your identity and that\'s why the default way of video calling is becoming unfavorable, so choosing a cartoony avatar is the most appealing option. \",\"In addition to that, face to face meeting is the most natural way to communicate. But if that\'s inconvenient, then video calling would be a preferable choice. People pay more attention when they can see the people they\'re talking to. Unfortunately despite all the benefits, video calling is incredibly easy to screw up. Well, that\'s not going to happen anymore. With the new beautification features of ChatGame, you won\'t have to adjust the lights or worry about how you look like while video calling. ChatGame takes the pressure away and instantly putting your best face forward! ChatGame\'s patent video effects provides a better and unique way for you to connect with anyone worldwide, while making sure you are having fun with a personal touch.\",\"Media Assets: http://tinyurl.com/ChatGameMediaAssets\",\"Youtube: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=6badB1vN47Q\",\"ChatGame is available in the AppStore and Google Play Store\",\"Join our Facebook for updates and events https://www.facebook.com/officialChatGame \",\"About ChatGame:\",\"Founded in 2014, ChatGame is fused together by passion, science, technology and art. We are a family, bonded by a goal and dream of changing the world.\",\"ChatGame\'s mission is to leverage the latest technologies to create innovative tools that will revolutionize the way people communicate with each other. We want to bring the joy of feeling connected in a world that is so vast, wherever you are.\",\"For more information, please contact: support@chatgame.me or visit our page https://www.facebook.com/officialChatGame \",\"For PR, please contact: riniasmara@chatgame.me\",\"Photo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151124/290564Photo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151124/290565 \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 16:23:44','2015-11-24 16:23:44',NULL),(11336,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/socialflow-appoints-david-u-simon-cmo-300182848.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/socialflow-appoints-david-u-simon-cmo-300182848.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/socialflow-appoints-david-u-simon-cmo-300182848.html\"],\"description\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Social media optimization company, SocialFlow, today announced the appointment of David U. Simon as Chief Marketing Officer. Simon will be responsible for leading all SocialFlow marketing efforts and will focus on refining the brand, expanding its publish\",\"content\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Social media optimization company, SocialFlow, today announced the appointment of David U. Simon as Chief Marketing Officer. Simon will be responsible for leading all SocialFlow marketing efforts and will focus on refining the brand, expanding its publish\",\"title\":\"SocialFlow Appoints David U. Simon CMO\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Social media optimization company, SocialFlow, today announced the appointment of David U. Simon as Chief Marketing Officer. Simon will be responsible for leading all SocialFlow marketing efforts and will focus on refining the brand, expanding its publishers market presence as well as both defining and marketing the recently released data-driven advertising products. Simon will join the company\'s New York based executive team, reporting to CEO, Jim Anderson.\",\"\\\"David is an enormously talented marketing executive, and his desire to join the SocialFlow team is a testament to our brand and its potential,\\\" said Jim Anderson, Chief Executive Officer for SocialFlow. \\\"His broad experience and success as a marketing strategist for major digital brands make him the ideal leader to help us scale our publisher presence and for the first time address the needs of advertisers.\\\"\",\"Simon comes to SocialFlow from PointRoll, (now a division of Sizmek) where he was also CMO. Simon started his digital media career as SVP of Sales for Seth Godin\'s Yoyodyne, later acquired by Yahoo!, where he ran Sales Programs then Promotions. He joined PointRoll as part of the acquisition of Boston-based Rovion, where he was President and CMO. Rovion, like PointRoll sold multi-screen, data-driven ad technology to major brands, their agencies and publishers.\",\"Mr. Simon said, \\\"SocialFlow knows more about what interests the social consumer in any given moment than anyone else. The opportunity to leverage this unique attention data and their powerful technology to create higher value relationships between consumers, publishes and brands is enormous. I am thrilled to join the SocialFlow team and look forward to being a part of the next chapter in data-driven social media marketing.\\\"\",\"About SocialFlow:SocialFlow is the premier social marketing platform, enabling the world\'s most powerful publishers and brands to drive superior results with their earned, owned and paid media strategies. Powered by predictive data analytics, the company offers a full suite of fully automated services in fifty-six languages that identify pre-trending, high value content, expand its audience engagement and amplify its social media distribution. Founded in 2009, New York-based SocialFlow works with numerous well-respected publishers such as The New York Times, The Wall Street Journal and the BBC as well as top brands including Microsoft, Stuart Weitzman and Birchbox. To learn more about SocialFlow, please visit us at http://www.socialflow.com.\",\"Photo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151120/289903 \",\"Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151120/289877LOGO \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 16:23:46','2015-11-24 16:23:46',NULL),(11337,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/bankers-healthcare-group-settles-in-at-its-new-corporate-headquarters-in-south-florida-300183937.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/bankers-healthcare-group-settles-in-at-its-new-corporate-headquarters-in-south-florida-300183937.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/bankers-healthcare-group-settles-in-at-its-new-corporate-headquarters-in-south-florida-300183937.html\"],\"description\":\"DAVIE, Fla., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Bankers Healthcare Group, the leading provider of financial solutions for healthcare professionals, has added more than 40 associates in South Florida over the past 12 months and plans to hire 50 more in the next 12. \\n\\n\\nThis past February, the company \",\"content\":\"DAVIE, Fla., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Bankers Healthcare Group, the leading provider of financial solutions for healthcare professionals, has added more than 40 associates in South Florida over the past 12 months and plans to hire 50 more in the next 12. \\n\\n\\nThis past February, the company \",\"title\":\"Bankers Healthcare Group Settles In At Its New Corporate Headquarters In South Florida\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"DAVIE, Fla., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Bankers Healthcare Group, the leading provider of financial solutions for healthcare professionals, has added more than 40 associates in South Florida over the past 12 months and plans to hire 50 more in the next 12. \",\"This past February, the company moved to new corporate headquarters in Davie, Florida and recently held a Grand Opening Celebration on Friday, August 21. Davie Mayor Judy Paul was in attendance. \\\"We are thrilled that you\'re here in the town of Davie,\\\" she told the crowd before cutting the ribbon with BHG co-founders and brothers Bob and Eric Castro. \",\"At the celebration, Broward Heart Walk Development Director Donna Byrne presented the company with a Gold Achievement Fit-Friendly Worksite Award on behalf of the American Heart Association. \\\"This award shows that you as employees are doing the right things for health and wellness, and you\'re working for a company who is educating you in wellness, which is one of the most important things for the American Heart Association: to spread the wealth into the community,\\\" she said.\",\"In addition, BHG President and Co-Founder Bob Castro presented a $10,000 check to the international relief and development organization, Food for the Poor, recently named the no. 1 charitable organization in South Florida by the South Florida Business Journal. BHG\'s relocation also provided a donation of more than 150 extra desks, chairs and other office furniture valued at $35,000. The furnishings were sent to Jamaica, where they have been repurposed in schools and orphanages supported by Food for the Poor. \",\"\\\"The greatest part about our growth as a company has been the increasing opportunity to give back,\\\" said Bob Castro. \\\"Food for the Poor is doing remarkable things to restore hope by meeting the needs of those in poverty or those facing disaster. We are proud to be one of their many supporters.\\\"\",\"\\\"The Grand Opening Celebration was a time to recognize how far we\'ve come and get energized by the amount of opportunity that lies ahead,\\\" said BHG Chief Operations Officer and Co-Founder Eric Castro. \\\"We owe our success to the dedication of every single member of the BHG family. We are truly grateful to be working with such talented, driven individuals.\\\"\",\"The new, modern space has generated buzz in publications such as The Boca Raton Observer and the Sun Sentinel and has received several awards for being an exciting, healthy workplace, including:\",\"The company has continued to expand since moving in February. Two adjacent buildings were renovated to create four modern and colorfully decorated floors of workstations, meeting rooms and recreation facilities. In keeping with BHG\'s dedication to employee fitness and healthy lifestyle, the company\'s 128 employees in Davie have access to:\",\"About Bankers Healthcare GroupSince 2001, Bankers Healthcare Group has been committed to providing hassle-free financial solutions to healthcare professionals, including personal and commercial loans, credit cards and insurance services. BHG has provided more than $2 billion in funding to thousands of satisfied customers nationwide. Inc. has recognized the company ten times for growth and job creation. For additional information, please visit www.bhg-inc.com.\",\"Contact: Pat Harrigan (315) 671-4129\",\"Video - https://youtu.be/px4_eZC2A9s Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20150323/183766LOGO\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 16:23:52','2015-11-24 16:23:52',NULL),(11338,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/strategy-analytics-top-3-smartphone-trends-predicted-for-2016-300183959.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/strategy-analytics-top-3-smartphone-trends-predicted-for-2016-300183959.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/strategy-analytics-top-3-smartphone-trends-predicted-for-2016-300183959.html\"],\"description\":\"BOSTON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;According to the latest research from Strategy Analytics, at least three major global shifts are predicted to take place in the smartphone market during 2016. Smartphone financing will become the norm, Indonesia will join India as the next big smartphone ma\",\"content\":\"BOSTON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;According to the latest research from Strategy Analytics, at least three major global shifts are predicted to take place in the smartphone market during 2016. Smartphone financing will become the norm, Indonesia will join India as the next big smartphone ma\",\"title\":\"Strategy Analytics: Top 3 Smartphone Trends Predicted for 2016\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"BOSTON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- According to the latest research from Strategy Analytics, at least three major global shifts are predicted to take place in the smartphone market during 2016. Smartphone financing will become the norm, Indonesia will join India as the next big smartphone market after China, and smartwatches will start to cannibalize fitness bands.\",\"Ken Hyers, Director at Strategy Analytics, said, \\\"Smartphone installment plans and lease-to-own programs will go global in 2016, as OEMs take programs that first gained traction in the United States to other markets. Apple iPhone Upgrade Program and ZTE SmartPay are among early leaders in using direct financing to boost smartphone shipments or enhance customer stickiness. Operators, like Sprint, will feel the squeeze from vendor-led financing and will need to respond vigorously with their own customer loyalty and lease-to-own programs.\\\"\",\"Neil Mawston, Executive Director at Strategy Analytics, added, \\\"Indonesia will join India as the next big smartphone market after China in 2016. As China\'s growth slows due to maturity, smartphone vendors will increasingly search for fresh growth in other emerging countries. India and Indonesia together will represent 13 percent of all smartphone shipments worldwide next year. India is set to overtake the United States as the second largest smartphone market by 2017. India and Indonesia will be the fastest-growing smartphone markets among the world\'s ten biggest countries from 2016 to 2020. We also predict some smartphone and component manufacturing to shift out of China and into India and Indonesia during the coming years, for closer supply proximity to these growing pools of demand.\\\"\",\"Cliff Raskind, Director at Strategy Analytics, added, \\\"In wearables, the Apple Watch will prove a relatively popular accessory for smartphone owners during the busy Q4 2015 holiday season and into 2016 when the next generation of smartwatch models will be launched. We forecast global smartwatch shipments to grow 57 percent in 2016, while fitness bands will grow just 8 percent next year. Smartwatches optimized for health and fitness, such as the Moto 360 Sport, are emerging as strong alternatives to Fitbit and other players in the fitness band category. Just as multi-function smartphones displaced most feature phones, multi-function smartwatches that support fitness apps, social feeds and music-to-go will eventually cannibalize mid-to-high-tier fitness bands.\\\"\",\"\",\"Exhibit 1: Top Global Smartphone Trends in 2016\",\"The full report, Top 10 Mobile Device Predictions for 2016, is published by the Strategy Analytics Wireless Device Strategies (WDS) service, details of which can be found here: http://tinyurl.com/oyxmrno.\",\"About Strategy Analytics:\",\"Strategy Analytics is a global, independent research and consulting firm. The company is headquartered in Boston, USA, with offices in the UK, France, Germany, Japan, South Korea, Taiwan, India and China. Visit www.strategyanalytics.com for more information.\",\"Americas Contacts:\",\"Ken Hyers / +1 617 614 0757 / KHyers@strategyanalytics.com \",\"Cliff Raskind / +1 617 614 0727 / CRaskind@strategyanalytics.com\",\"EMEA Contact:\",\"Neil Mawston / +44 1908 423 628 