th supplements for women, it was revealed that stress on the body increases the need for important vitamins such as Vitamin D and E. The DHA has said that more than half of Dubai residents are not consuming enough to keep themselves healthy. A local expert addressed how a poor diet and sedentary lifestyle can cause stress on the body that actually increases a women\'s need for certain vitamins and minerals. Safeguarding one\'s health and ensuring nutritional balance in today\'s urban lifestyle can be easily achieved by taking targeted and condition-specific supplements developed by femMED.\",\"At the roundtable discussion on women\'s health in the UAE, Dr. Baher Massoud, Chief Medical Officer - Africa, Middle East &amp; Turkey, NewBridge Pharmaceuticals, and femMED spokesperson said: \",\"\\\"By developing supplements that target specific areas of women\'s health, such as Bone Health or Hair, Skin and Nails, we are helping women identify and select a product that is suitable for their individual needs. Women pay attention to the condition of their bodies, but may not realize that oftentimes, poor quality nails and brittle hair is a clear sign that there is nutrition lacking in the body. Our aim is to educate the local community on how and when supplements should be taken, and how they can be best used to address common health concerns.\\\"   \",\"femMED health supplements for women is a specific range of supplements designed specially to address women\'s most common health concerns at every stage of her life. Well-known for providing comprehensive solutions, femMED\'s supplements contain natural vitamins, minerals, and herbs. The products are free of dairy, egg, artificial colors and flavors, and most are gluten free. The capsules are vegetable based. Five of femMED\'s 20 formulations are now available in the UAE market.\",\"Dr. Dana Al-Hamwi, Clinical Dietician at Dr. Dana\'s Diet Clinic, addressed dieting in the UAE and the related nutritional concerns: \",\"\\\"Women in the UAE have very busy lifestyles and therefore don\'t have enough time to prepare healthy meals. There is an 80% increase in junk food consumption.  Because most of the foods consumed are empty calorie foods, many important vitamins are often not consumed in adequate portions. The stress on the body due to lacking nutrients is compounded with a sedentary lifestyle, which can increase her body\'s requirements for some nutrients such as Magnesium, Vitamin D, and Vitamin E.\\\"   \",\"femMED\'s solutions are developed by doctors, and are easily recognized and understood by consumers. By eliminating the \'guess work\' often associated with supplements, femMED can ensure that women are only consuming what they actually require.\",\"Dr. Al-Hamwi continued: \\\"As much as 75% of people in the UAE or either overweight or obese.  There is no question that all people should make a habit of eating healthily, but supplements are an effective way of boosting the immune system and replenishing supplies of rapidly depleting nutrients. Supplements should always be taken in partnership with a healthy diet - not as an alternative.\\\" \",\"Manufactured in Canada, femMED\'s comprehensive solutions stand out in a market dominated by single-ingredient products. In the UAE, five supplement lines are available, including Bone Health; Hair, Skin, and Nails; Pregnancy; Pregnancy + Ginger; and Multi + Antioxidants.\",\"About femMED \",\"Founded in 2007, femMED is a brand of comprehensive supplements designed specifically for the unique needs of women. femMED\'s line of 20 doctor-formulated remedies provide natural solutions to women\'s most common health concerns, at every age and stage of life. Five of these remedies are currently available in the UAE. Each product contains only the highest quality vitamins, minerals and herbs, with each ingredient backed by extensive research and clinical studies. All femMED formulations are free of gluten, dairy, egg, artificial colors and flavors, and almost all are yeast-free, suitable for vegetarians and delivered in vegetable capsules. femMED formulas are designed to work on their own, or in combination with other femMED formulas to achieve multiple health goals. All products are produced in Canadian pharmaceutically licensed facilities. For more information about femMED supplements, please visit http://www.femmed.com.\",\"About NewBridge Pharmaceuticals \",\"NewBridge Pharmaceuticals is a first-in-class specialty therapeutics company focused on pharmaceuticals, biologics, medical diagnostics and other innovative healthcare products serving the AfMET markets (Africa, Middle East and Turkey) to address the unmet medical needs of diseases with high regional prevalence. Headquartered in the UAE with strong local and international business network, NewBridge is uniquely positioned as the partner-of-choice for pharmaceutical, biotechnology and other healthcare companies seeking to create value for their pharma or medical products in the high growth emerging AfMET markets.\",\"For more information, please visit http://www.nbpharma.com.\",\"For media inquiries only, please contact: \\nIbrahim Mougharbel\\nInstinctif Partners\\nIbrahim.mougharbel@instinctif.com\\n+971-4-369-9353\\n\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:05:02','2015-11-24 17:05:02',NULL),(11409,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/tata-technologies-named-global-rd-leader-300183867.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 08:07:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 08:07:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/tata-technologies-named-global-rd-leader-300183867.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/tata-technologies-named-global-rd-leader-300183867.html\"],\"description\":\"MUMBAI, India, Nov. 24,&#160;2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Tata Technologies, a leading product development and engineering services firm, has been named a global engineering and IT outsourcing leader in Zinnov\'s 2015 Global R&amp;D Service Providers Ratings.\\n\\nTata Technologies received high overall mar\",\"content\":\"MUMBAI, India, Nov. 24,&#160;2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;Tata Technologies, a leading product development and engineering services firm, has been named a global engineering and IT outsourcing leader in Zinnov\'s 2015 Global R&amp;D Service Providers Ratings.\\n\\nTata Technologies received high overall mar\",\"title\":\"Tata Technologies Named Global R&amp;D Leader\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"MUMBAI, India, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Tata Technologies, a leading product development and engineering services firm, has been named a global engineering and IT outsourcing leader in Zinnov\'s 2015 Global R&amp;D Service Providers Ratings.\",\"Tata Technologies received high overall marks across all selected categories based on breadth and depth of service capabilities and high delivery standards. In the automotive and the construction and heavy machinery sectors, the company was given standout positions and recognised as a clear and established global leader. This ranking underlines the company\'s strengths in the areas of domain expertise, innovation and customer co-creation.\",\"Tata Technologies Chief Marketing and Strategy Officer Richard Welford said: \",\"\\\"This is a testament to the hard work, dedication and diverse expertise of our teams around the globe. We are clearly established as leaders in the automotive and construction and heavy machinery verticals, and we are now also emerging as a leader in the aerospace sector, where we see considerable potential for growth.\",\"\\\"Zinnov is widely respected in our industry and, most importantly, by our customers. This report recognises the significance of our core industry value propositions for manufacturers seeking a strategic engineering and innovation partner.\\\"\",\"Sidhant Rastogi, Partner and Practice Head of Zinnov, said: \",\"\\\"Tata Technologies has emerged as one of the globally dominant players in the mechanical and manufacturing engineering services space. Their engineering partnerships  with global enterprises in critical large scale R&amp;D programs  and their ability to execute end-to-end product development programs is what makes Tata Technologies stand out as a leading player in the automotive and heavy machinery services sectors. \",\"\\\"Furthermore, a globally diversified delivery model with presence across multiple near-shore and onshore locations makes Tata Technologies a preferred partner to organizations seeking global product development and engineering support.\\\"\",\"About Tata Technologies\",\"Tata Technologies is a global engineering services firm that provides product development, product lifecycle management, and enterprise resource planning products and services for many of the world\'s most successful manufacturers. In the last financial year, Tata Technologies generated over $424 million in consolidated revenue with more than 8,000 professionals serving clients in North America, Europe and the Asia-Pacific region. Tata Technologies operates as part of the wider Tata group adhering to and sharing the group\'s values. \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:11:56','2015-11-24 17:11:56',NULL),(11410,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/abaxis-inc-to-present-at-the-27th-annual-piper-jaffray-healthcare-conference-300183757.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 08:00:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 08:00:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/abaxis-inc-to-present-at-the-27th-annual-piper-jaffray-healthcare-conference-300183757.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/abaxis-inc-to-present-at-the-27th-annual-piper-jaffray-healthcare-conference-300183757.html\"],\"description\":\"UNION CITY, Calif., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Abaxis, Inc. (NasdaqGS: ABAX), a global diagnostics company manufacturing point-of-care instruments and consumables for the medical, research, and veterinary markets worldwide, announced today that Ross Taylor, Chief Financial Officer, will present a\",\"content\":\"UNION CITY, Calif., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Abaxis, Inc. (NasdaqGS: ABAX), a global diagnostics company manufacturing point-of-care instruments and consumables for the medical, research, and veterinary markets worldwide, announced today that Ross Taylor, Chief Financial Officer, will present a\",\"title\":\"Abaxis, Inc. to Present at the 27th Annual Piper Jaffray Healthcare Conference\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"UNION CITY, Calif., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Abaxis, Inc. (NasdaqGS:  ABAX), a global diagnostics company manufacturing point-of-care instruments and consumables for the medical, research, and veterinary markets worldwide, announced today that Ross Taylor, Chief Financial Officer, will present at the 27th Annual Piper Jaffray Healthcare Conference on Tuesday, December 1, 2015 at 11:30 a.m. ET. The conference will be held at The Lotte New York Palace in New York City.\",\"About AbaxisAbaxis, Inc. is a worldwide developer, manufacturer and marketer of portable blood analysis systems that are used in a broad range of medical specialties in human or veterinary patient care to provide clinicians with rapid blood constituent measurements.  Our mission is to improve the efficiency of care delivery to and the quality of life of patients in the medical and veterinary markets.  We provide leading edge technology, tools and services that support best medical practices, enabling physicians and veterinarians to respond to the health needs of their clients at the point of care while operating economical and profitable practices.  For more information, visit http://www.abaxis.com.\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"no\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:13:54','2015-11-24 17:13:54',NULL),(11411,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/nasa-tv-coverage-set-for-fourth-orbital-atk-resupply-mission-to-space-station-300183982.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:37:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:37:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/nasa-tv-coverage-set-for-fourth-orbital-atk-resupply-mission-to-space-station-300183982.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/nasa-tv-coverage-set-for-fourth-orbital-atk-resupply-mission-to-space-station-300183982.html\"],\"description\":\"WASHINGTON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ --&#160;NASA commercial partner Orbital ATK is targeting Thursday, Dec. 3, for the launch of its fourth contracted mission to the International Space Station under the agency\'s Commercial Resupply Services contract. NASA Television coverage of the la\",\"content\":\"WASHINGTON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ --&#160;NASA commercial partner Orbital ATK is targeting Thursday, Dec. 3, for the launch of its fourth contracted mission to the International Space Station under the agency\'s Commercial Resupply Services contract. NASA Television coverage of the la\",\"title\":\"NASA TV Coverage Set for Fourth Orbital ATK Resupply Mission to Space Station\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"WASHINGTON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ -- NASA commercial partner Orbital ATK is targeting Thursday, Dec. 3, for the launch of its fourth contracted mission to the International Space Station under the agency\'s Commercial Resupply Services contract. NASA Television coverage of the launch begins at 4:30 p.m. EST.\",\"The company\'s Cygnus spacecraft is set to lift off on a United Launch Alliance Atlas V rocket at 5:55 p.m., the beginning of a 30-minute launch window, from Space Launch Complex 41 on Cape Canaveral Air Force Station in Florida. Cygnus will carry more than 7,000 pounds of science and research, crew supplies and vehicle hardware to the orbital laboratory to support dozens of approximately 250 science and research investigations that will occur during Expeditions 45 and 46. This first Cygnus mission using the Atlas V launch system provides increased performance and flexibility to the Orbital ATK cargo delivery service.\",\"In addition to launch coverage, NASA TV will air three briefings Wednesday, Dec. 2: several experts involved in the launch and mission will host an interactive discussion with the agency\'s social media followers from 9 to 10:30 a.m.; at 1 p.m., scientists and researchers will discuss some of the investigations to be delivered; at 2 p.m., mission managers will host a prelaunch news conference. A post-launch briefing will be held approximately two hours after launch. All briefings will air live on NASA TV and the agency\'s website. \",\"The new experiments arriving to the orbiting laboratory will challenge and inspire future scientists and explorers. Science payloads will offer a new life science facility that will support studies on cell cultures, bacteria and other microorganisms; a microsatellite deployer and the first microsatellite that will be deployed from the space station; and experiments that will study the behavior of gases and liquids, clarify the thermo-physical properties of molten steel, and evaluate flame-resistant textiles. \",\"Cygnus also will deliver replacement cargo items including a set of Microsoft HoloLens devices for use in NASA\'s Sidekick project, a safety jet pack astronauts wear during spacewalks known as SAFER, and high pressure nitrogen and oxygen tanks to plug into the station\'s air supply network.\",\"This will be the first flight of an enhanced Cygnus spacecraft to the station. The cargo freighter now features a greater payload capacity, new UltraFlexTM solar arrays and new fuel tanks. Cygnus\' pressurized cargo module has been extended and increases the spacecraft\'s interior volume capacity by 25 percent, enabling more cargo to be delivered with each mission. \",\"A Dec. 3 launch will result in the Cygnus spacecraft arriving at the space station on Sunday, Dec. 6. NASA crew members Kjell Lindgren and Scott Kelly will use the station\'s Canadarm2 robotic arm to reach out and capture Cygnus at approximately 5:30 a.m. NASA TV coverage of rendezvous and grapple of Cygnus will begin at 4 a.m. Cygnus will be the first cargo ship to be berthed to the Earth-facing port on the Unity module. Coverage of Cygnus\' installation will begin at 7:15 a.m.  \",\"The spacecraft will spend more than a month attached to the space station before its destructive reentry into Earth\'s atmosphere in January 2016, disposing of about 3,000 pounds of trash. \",\"If the launch does not occur on Dec. 3, the next launch opportunity would be at 5:33 p.m. on Friday, Dec. 4, resulting in a grapple and berthing on Dec. 7 or Dec. 8.\",\"Media at the agency\'s Kennedy Space Center in Florida also will have the opportunity to participate in tours on Tuesday, Dec. 1. Journalists will see the progress being made on NASA\'s Commercial Crew Program, which will return astronaut launches from U.S. soil to the space station, as well as the ground systems to support the Space Launch System rocket for missions to deep space and eventually on the journey to Mars. The deadline for media to apply for accreditation has passed. For more information about media accreditation, contact Jennifer Horner at 321-867-6598 or jennifer.p.horner@nasa.gov. \",\"For an updated schedule of prelaunch briefings, events and NASA TV coverage, visit:\",\"http://go.nasa.gov/1MzW1Cj\",\"For NASA TV schedule and video streaming information, visit:\",\"http://www.nasa.gov/nasatv\",\"For launch countdown coverage, NASA\'s launch blog, and more information about the mission, visit:\",\"http://www.nasa.gov/orbitalatk \",\"For more information about the International Space Station, visit:\",\"http://www.nasa.gov/station\",\"Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20081007/38461LOGO\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"neutral\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:13:56','2015-11-24 17:13:56',NULL),(11412,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/investor-alert-levi--korsinsky-llp-notifies-shareholders-of-telecommunications-systems-inc-of-an-investigation-regarding-the-fairness-of-the-sale-of-the-company-to-comtech-telecommunications-corp----tsys-300183987.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 11:47:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 11:47:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/investor-alert-levi--korsinsky-llp-notifies-shareholders-of-telecommunications-systems-inc-of-an-investigation-regarding-the-fairness-of-the-sale-of-the-company-to-comtech-telecommunications-corp----tsys-300183987.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/investor-alert-levi--korsinsky-llp-notifies-shareholders-of-telecommunications-systems-inc-of-an-investigation-regarding-the-fairness-of-the-sale-of-the-company-to-comtech-telecommunications-corp----tsys-300183987.html\"],\"description\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ --&#160;The following statement is being issued by Levi &amp; Korsinsky, LLP:\\n\\n\\nTo: All Persons or Entities who purchased TeleCommunications Systems, Inc. (NASDAQ: TSYS) stock prior to November 23, 2015.\\n\\nYou are hereby notified that Levi &amp; Korsins\",\"content\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ --&#160;The following statement is being issued by Levi &amp; Korsinsky, LLP:\\n\\n\\nTo: All Persons or Entities who purchased TeleCommunications Systems, Inc. (NASDAQ: TSYS) stock prior to November 23, 2015.\\n\\nYou are hereby notified that Levi &amp; Korsins\",\"title\":\"INVESTOR ALERT: Levi &amp; Korsinsky, LLP Notifies Shareholders of TeleCommunications Systems, Inc. of an Investigation Regarding the Fairness of the Sale of the Company to Comtech Telecommunications Corp. -- TSYS\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\