e verklaringen.\",\" \",\"Media relations: Debora de Laaf, +31(0)70-344-8730, gcc@aegon.com ; Investor relations: Willem van den Berg, +31(0)70-344-8405, ir@aegon.com\",\"    PR NLD\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:01','2015-11-24 17:59:01',NULL),(11458,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/toy-workers-still-suffering-widespread-abuses-300184005.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:34:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:34:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/toy-workers-still-suffering-widespread-abuses-300184005.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/toy-workers-still-suffering-widespread-abuses-300184005.html\"],\"description\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ --&#160;China Labor Watch (CLW) has released a 123-page investigative report (PDF) of five toy factories in China, finding 29 sets of labor abuses, at least 21 of which violate Chinese law. The factories supply to Hasbro, Mattel and Mattel-owned Fisher\",\"content\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ --&#160;China Labor Watch (CLW) has released a 123-page investigative report (PDF) of five toy factories in China, finding 29 sets of labor abuses, at least 21 of which violate Chinese law. The factories supply to Hasbro, Mattel and Mattel-owned Fisher\",\"title\":\"Toy Workers Still Suffering Widespread Abuses\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire-USNewswire/ -- China Labor Watch (CLW) has released a 123-page investigative report (PDF) of five toy factories in China, finding 29 sets of labor abuses, at least 21 of which violate Chinese law. The factories supply to Hasbro, Mattel and Mattel-owned Fisher Price, McDonald\'s, Jakks Pacific, Disney, NSI Toys, Battat, MGA Entertainment, and Walmart.\",\"Based on investigative findings, CLW has also released the Sweatshop Toy List, which describes the factory working conditions under which various popular toys are made. In the run-up to the holiday season, CLW will continue to populate the Sweatshop Toy List with toys actually observed in investigated factories. The objective of the toy list is to inform the public about the way in which popular toys made by workers that suffer regular rights infringements.         \",\"CLW emphasizes that the toy industry has been sourcing from Chinese factories for 20 years, during which time the industry has touted legal and fair treatment of workers. Yet in 2015, CLW continues to observe the failure among toy industry leaders to ensure some fundamental legal rights for workers, to say nothing of fair treatment. \",\"The major toy brand and retail companies have the power to influence and control labor conditions in toy factories. They must institute fundamental reforms which include but are not limited to:\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:03','2015-11-24 17:59:03',NULL),(11459,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/namic-announces-newly-elected-board-directors-300184008.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:37:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:37:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/namic-announces-newly-elected-board-directors-300184008.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/namic-announces-newly-elected-board-directors-300184008.html\"],\"description\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- NAMIC (National Association for Multi-ethnicity in Communications) today announced the addition of five Directors to its Board. The elected Directors will begin serving three-year terms on January 1, 2016.\\n\\n\\nThe newly elected members of the NAMIC National Boar\",\"content\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- NAMIC (National Association for Multi-ethnicity in Communications) today announced the addition of five Directors to its Board. The elected Directors will begin serving three-year terms on January 1, 2016.\\n\\n\\nThe newly elected members of the NAMIC National Boar\",\"title\":\"NAMIC Announces Newly Elected Board Directors\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- NAMIC (National Association for Multi-ethnicity in Communications) today announced the addition of five Directors to its Board. The elected Directors will begin serving three-year terms on January 1, 2016.\",\"The newly elected members of the NAMIC National Board of Directors are: James Brown, SVP, Head of Content Distribution, Revolt TV; Jay R. Grant, SVP, Associate General Counsel, Univision Communications, Inc.; Mark Kang, SVP, Worldwide Distribution, INSP TV; Indrajit Ponnambalam, Group VP, Finance, Time Warner Cable; and Ninoska Zucconi, VP, Distribution Marketing, Univision Communications, Inc.\",\"\\\"NAMIC is honored to welcome these distinguished executives to the board,\\\" said Michelle L. Rice, Chair, NAMIC National Board of Directors and EVP, Content Distribution &amp; Marketing, TV One.  \\\"The expertise and professional experience that this group of diversity champions embodies is invaluable. With their support and guidance we look forward to advancing our mission.\\\"\",\"The Directors set to begin serving terms January 1, 2016 as members of the Board\'s Executive Committee are: Chair - Michelle L. Rice, EVP, Content Distribution &amp; Marketing, TV One; Vice Chair - Kevin Stephens, President, Commercial &amp; Advertising Operations, Suddenlink Communications; Secretary - Ebonne Ruffins, Sr. Director, Diversity Communications, Comcast Corporation; Treasurer - Mark DePietro, VP, Business Development, ARRIS; Immediate Past Chair - Michael D. Armstrong, EVP &amp; GM, International Brand Development, Viacom International Media Networks; and Eglon E. Simons, President &amp; CEO, NAMIC National. \",\"Additional members of the NAMIC National Board of Directors include: James L. Anderson, SVP, Communications, Turner Broadcasting System, Inc.; Michael Cooper, VP, Distribution Marketing, FOX Networks Group; Oliver Dizon, SVP, Asset Management, ESPN; Alana Moton Leverette, Marketing Director, Business Services - Big South Region, Comcast; Carla Moore, VP, Talent Acquisition, HBO; Yasmine M. Ndassa, Sr. Director, Business Process Analytics, Comcast; Janet Parker, VP, Human Resources, Time Warner Cable; Belinda Turner Patterson, VP, People Services, Cox Communications; Jaime J. Rodriguez, VP, Business &amp; Legal Affairs, NBC Universal; Ashok Sinha, VP, Global Brand Reputation &amp; Corporate Communications, Starcom MediaVest Group; Michelle Strong, SVP, Distribution, National Accounts, A+E Networks; Wanda E. Townsend, VP, Government Relations, National Cable &amp; Telecommunications Association; Danielle Wade, VP &amp; GM, Brighthouse Networks; Crystal B. Washington, SVP, External Relations &amp; Vendor Management, Scripps Networks Interactive; Donna Rattley Washington, Regional VP, Government &amp; Regulatory Affairs, Washington Metro Area, Comcast Cable; and Lisa Williams-Fauntroy, SVP, Business &amp; Legal Affairs, Discovery Communications. \",\"For more information on the National Association for Multi-ethnicity in Communications and its Board of Directors visit www.namic.com or contact the NAMIC National headquarters at 212-594-5985.\",\"ABOUT NAMIC NAMIC (National Association for Multi-ethnicity in Communications) is the premier organization focusing on multi-ethnic diversity in the communications industry. Founded in 1980 as a non-profit trade association, today NAMIC comprises 2,700 professionals belonging to a network of 16 chapters nationwide. Through initiatives that focus on education, advocacy and empowerment, NAMIC champions equity and inclusion in the workforce, with special attention given to ensuring that the leadership cadres of our nation\'s communications industry giants reflect the multi-ethnic richness of the populations they serve. Comcast | NBCUniversal, Time Warner Cable and Turner Broadcasting System, Inc. are NAMIC\'s Platinum Annual Corporate Sponsors. For more information, please visit www.namic.com and stay connected to NAMIC on Facebook, LinkedIn, and Twitter. \",\"MEDIA CONTACT Charmaine Chapman BTB Communications 310-882-5498 ext. 5 (office) char@btbcommunications.com \",\"Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20060705/NYW092LOGO \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:04','2015-11-24 17:59:04',NULL),(11460,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/mcglinchey-staffords-intellectual-propertycommercial-litigation-team-adds-seasoned-ip-attorney-john-ohman-to-new-york-city-office-300184010.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:38:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:38:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/mcglinchey-staffords-intellectual-propertycommercial-litigation-team-adds-seasoned-ip-attorney-john-ohman-to-new-york-city-office-300184010.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/mcglinchey-staffords-intellectual-propertycommercial-litigation-team-adds-seasoned-ip-attorney-john-ohman-to-new-york-city-office-300184010.html\"],\"description\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;McGlinchey Stafford PLLC is happy to announce that 20-year attorney John C. Ohman has joined the firm\'s New York City office as Of Counsel. Ohman will practice within the firm\'s national Intellectual Property and Commercial Litigation practice groups.\\n\\n\\nO\",\"content\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;McGlinchey Stafford PLLC is happy to announce that 20-year attorney John C. Ohman has joined the firm\'s New York City office as Of Counsel. Ohman will practice within the firm\'s national Intellectual Property and Commercial Litigation practice groups.\\n\\n\\nO\",\"title\":\"McGlinchey Stafford\'s Intellectual Property/Commercial Litigation Team Adds Seasoned IP Attorney John Ohman to New York City Office\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- McGlinchey Stafford PLLC is happy to announce that 20-year attorney John C. Ohman has joined the firm\'s New York City office as Of Counsel. Ohman will practice within the firm\'s national Intellectual Property and Commercial Litigation practice groups.\",\"Ohman is an experienced litigator whose law practice spans more than 20 years, focusing on complex technology, commercial, and business litigation. He has litigated a broad range of cases involving trademarks, copyrights, patents, trade secrets, restrictive covenants, antitrust, Racketeer Influenced and Corrupt Organizations Act (RICO), fiduciary breaches, real estate, construction litigation, and close corporation and partnership disputes, as well as employment, legal malpractice, and business torts. He has extensive experience in disputes arising from the failure of computer software and other high-technology implementation projects. Separately, Ohman has represented clients in numerous proceedings before the American Arbitration Association and other arbitration authorities. \",\"\\\"We\'re delighted to welcome John to our New York City office, and to our expanding Intellectual Property and Commercial Litigation teams,\\\" said Anthony Rollo, Chair of the firm\'s national Commercial Litigation practice group. \\\"John\'s broad and deep litigation experience complements our existing New York practice and also adds significant strength to our national practice groups. His insight and experience representing companies in a wide range of high-tech disputes and complex litigation provide tremendous value to our clients, and adding him to our thriving New York business is a major win for our clients,\\\" Rollo added. \",\"Prior to entering the legal field, Ohman spent nearly 10 years working in the financial services industry, chiefly in the operational areas of trades processing and reconciliation. Following law school, Ohman began his legal career at Brown Raysman &amp; Millstein and remained at that firm after its merger with Thelen Reid &amp; Priest in 2006. At Brown Raysman, he served as General Counsel and Litigation Department Assignment Partner while maintaining an active litigation practice. Ohman earned his J.D. from the Columbia University School of Law in 1992 and his B.A. from Columbia University in 1978. \",\"\\\"My clients\' needs have continued to evolve in a changing and competitive marketplace,\\\" said Ohman. \\\"McGlinchey Stafford has the legal expertise, bench depth, and geographic reach to meet those needs across core litigation and transactional practice disciplines. I am excited to join this dynamic and growing firm,\\\" Ohman added. \",\"McGlinchey Stafford\'s New York City office was established in 2014 to better serve the legal needs of key clients in the areas of financial services, business, and general civil litigation, while expanding the firm\'s regional footprint in the Northeast. The firm\'s New York City office has grown by seven attorneys in 2015 to its current headcount of 13 attorneys following the addition of Ohman. The firm also has an office in Albany, with four attorneys.\",\"ABOUT MCGLINCHEY STAFFORDMcGlinchey Stafford is a full-service law firm providing innovative legal counsel to business clients nationwide. Guiding clients wherever business and law intersect, McGlinchey Stafford\'s 200 attorneys are based in 13 offices in Alabama, California, Florida, Louisiana, Mississippi, New York, Ohio, Texas, and Washington, DC. To learn more about McGlinchey Stafford, visit www.mcglinchey.com. \",\"Photo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151124/290674\",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:06','2015-11-24 17:59:06',NULL),(11461,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/firstenergys-power-plants-prepared-to-operate-reliably-through-winter-weather-300184012.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:38:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:38:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/firstenergys-power-plants-prepared-to-operate-reliably-through-winter-weather-300184012.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/firstenergys-power-plants-prepared-to-operate-reliably-through-winter-weather-300184012.html\"],\"description\":\"AKRON, Ohio, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Fifteen generating stations owned by FirstEnergy Corp. (NYSE: FE) in Ohio, Pennsylvania and West Virginia today have completed comprehensive preventive maintenance work to help ensure they are well-prepared to deliver reliable operations throughout winter, \",\"content\":\"AKRON, Ohio, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Fifteen generating stations owned by FirstEnergy Corp. (NYSE: FE) in Ohio, Pennsylvania and West Virginia today have completed comprehensive preventive maintenance work to help ensure they are well-prepared to deliver reliable operations throughout winter, \",\"title\":\"FirstEnergy\'s Power Plants Prepared to Operate Reliably through Winter Weather\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"AKRON, Ohio, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Fifteen generating stations owned by FirstEnergy Corp. (NYSE:  FE) in Ohio, Pennsylvania and West Virginia today have completed comprehensive preventive maintenance work to help ensure they are well-prepared to deliver reliable operations throughout winter, when electricity demand is higher due to increased heating needs.   \",\"\\\"FirstEnergy\'s diverse generating fleet has consistently provided electricity to customers in recent winters when our region was tested with extreme temperatures,\\\" said Jim Lash, president, FirstEnergy Generation.  \\\"In fact, our plants operated reliably when a new peak demand record was set in February 2015, and they are again prepared to deliver during winter conditions this year.\\\"\",\"In addition to its three nuclear power plants, six coal-fired generating stations, and six oil and natural gas plants, FirstEnergy owns or controls electricity generation at nine hydro and wind facilities for a total capacity of nearly 17,000 megawatts across Ohio, Pennsylvania, West Virginia, New Jersey, Virginia and Illinois. Collectively, these assets produced nearly 24.5 million megawatt hours of electricity from July through September 2015, the hottest months of the year.  (One megawatt powers approximately 1,000 homes.)  Continued strong performance throughout the winter months will help ensure FirstEnergy is well-positioned to meet demand peaks such as those experienced during recent harsh winters. \",\"To prepare for frigid temperatures and icy conditions, plant operators installed storm barriers to protect plant equipment from winter weather, set up heating elements that provide additional warmth to piping, provided temporary heaters in areas most susceptible to cold, added anti-freeze to equipment, and increased fuel stockpiles at coal-fired facilities.  \",\"Throughout the winter, operators run water pumps more often to avoid freezing, keep oil flow within transformers more constant, and take precautions to prevent cooling towers from icing.  FirstEnergy will also stay in close contact with PJM Interconnection, L.L.C., the regional grid operator, to avoid scheduling plant maintenance work during periods of high electricity demand.\",\"Winter preparations also were supported by a number of long-term reliability projects completed at FirstEnergy generating facilities this year.  A new, large transformer that connects Beaver Valley with the electrical grid was delivered to the plant this fall, where it will be maintained as a spare that can be quickly and efficiently installed should there be an issue with one of the two transformers in use.  In addition, the company spent more than $60 million on reliability upgrades at its Springdale natural gas plant in southwest Pennsylvania, ensuring the facility will generate affordable and low-emitting electricity for years to come.\",\"FirstEnergy is a diversified energy company dedicated to safety, reliability and operational excellence. Its 10 electric distribution companies form one of the nation\'s largest investor-owned electric systems, serving customers in Ohio, Pennsylvania, New Jersey, West Virginia, Maryland and New York. Follow FirstEnergy on Twitter @FirstEnergyCorp.\",\"Editor\'s Note:  Photos of some of the reliability projects at FirstEnergy\'s generating stations are available for download on Flickr.\",\"www.firstenergycorp.com \",\" \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:07','2015-11-24 17:59:07',NULL),(11462,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/analysis-of-smart-city-opportunities-in-latin-america-300184009.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:38:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:38:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/analysis-of-smart-city-opportunities-in-latin-america-300184009.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/analysis-of-smart-city-opportunities-in-latin-america-300184009.html\"],\"description\":\"LONDON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Analysis of Smart City Opportunities in Latin America : Case Studies Indicate the Concept is Slowly Gaining Traction in the RegionExecutive Summary-As cities grow and become metropolises or megalopolises, they must confront challenges related to energy and water\",\"content\":\"LONDON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Analysis of Smart City Opportunities in Latin America : Case Studies Indicate the Concept is Slowly Gaining Traction in the RegionExecutive Summary-As cities grow and become metropolises or megalopolises, they must confront challenges related to energy and water\",\"title\":\"Analysis of Smart City Opportunities in Latin America\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"LONDON, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Analysis of Smart City Opportunities in Latin America : Case Studies Indicate the Concept is Slowly Gaining Traction in the RegionExecutive Summary-As cities grow and become metropolises or megalopolises, they must confront challenges related to energy and water availability, general infrastructure, sanitation, health, and other basic services. - While many cities want to become smart cities, most of their initiatives center on green concepts only. Smart cities apply technology to become more efficient in the use of resources, saving energy, improving services, and promoting sustainable development.- The goal of a smart city is to solve major problems that citizens face daily through modernized management that encourages greater interaction between citizens and institutions to achieve better quality of life.- The smart city concept is still developing in Latin America as many cities confront problems such as drug trafficking, pollution, and congestion. Management is not known for efficiency, and there is much less transparency than in cities located in more developed regions.Frost &amp; Sullivan analysts reviewed numerous smart city projects and initiatives being undertaken globally and found 8 parameters that were indicative of what constitutes a smart city. Frost &amp; Sullivan has defined smart cities as those that are built on \\\"smart\\\" and \\\"intelligent\\\" solutions and technology that will lead to adoption of at least out of parameters: smart governance and smart education, smart energy, smart building, smart mobility, smart infrastructure, smart technology, smart healthcare, and smart citizen. - This study identifies key smart cities in Latin America, what has been done in their development, and the long path to follow. It details the most relevant initiatives in the region.Download the full report: https://www.reportbuyer.com/product/3398346/About ReportbuyerReportbuyer is a leading industry intelligence solution that provides all market research reports from top publishershttp://www.reportbuyer.com\",\"For more information: Sarah Smith Research Advisor at Reportbuyer.com Email: query@reportbuyer.com  Tel: +44 208 816 85 48 Website: www.reportbuyer.com \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:09','2015-11-24 17:59:09',NULL),(11463,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/happy-code-escola-de-programacao-e-robotica-para-criancas-e-jovens-anuncia-plano-de-expansao-com-unidades-em-todo-estado-de-sao-paulo-553185061.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:40:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:40:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/happy-code-escola-de-programacao-e-robotica-para-criancas-e-jovens-anuncia-plano-de-expansao-com-unidades-em-todo-estado-de-sao-paulo-553185061.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/happy-code-escola-de-programacao-e-robotica-para-criancas-e-jovens-anuncia-plano-de-expansao-com-unidades-em-todo-estado-de-sao-paulo-553185061.html\"],\"description\":\"CAMPINAS, Brasil, 24 de novembro de 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- A Happy Code apresenta um m&#233;todo de ensino inovador como escola especializada no ensino de programa&#231;&#227;o e rob&#243;tica para crian&#231;as e jovens, por esta raz&#227;o vem se destacando no mercado de educa&#231;&#227;o. \\n\\nPor co\",\"content\":\"CAMPINAS, Brasil, 24 de novembro de 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- A Happy Code apresenta um m&#233;todo de ensino inovador como escola especializada no ensino de programa&#231;&#227;o e rob&#243;tica para crian&#231;as e jovens, por esta raz&#227;o vem se destacando no mercado de educa&#231;&#227;o. \\n\\nPor co\",\"title\":\"Happy Code, escola de programação e robótica para crianças e jovens, anuncia plano de expansão com unidades em todo estado de São Paulo\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"CAMPINAS, Brasil, 24 de novembro de 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- A Happy Code apresenta um método de ensino inovador como escola especializada no ensino de programação e robótica para crianças e jovens, por esta razão vem se destacando no mercado de educação. \",\"Por conta da importância deste ensino e da demanda crescente, a escola anunciou uma expansão agressiva com a inauguração de mais unidades próprias. A Happy Code foi inaugurada em junho deste ano, na cidade de Valinhos, interior do Estado de São Paulo. Neste mês de novembro, inaugura a sua sede em Campinas, que será o maior centro de ensino de tecnologia para crianças e jovens do país. \",\"Para o fundador da escola, Rodrigo Santos, a expansão para outras localidades é essencial para garantir o acesso do ensino de programação e robótica para todos. Também, implantar este ensino no Brasil é fundamental para o futuro profissional e pessoal dos estudantes. \\\"No início de 2016 vamos inaugurar mais 6 novas unidades: Vinhedo-SP e Jundiaí-SP no interior paulista, e nos bairros Vila Mariana, Moema e Higienópolis na cidade de São Paulo, além de uma unidade em Alphaville\\\", contou Santos. \",\"A escola oferece um curso desenvolvido com plataforma americana adaptada com um plano de aulas para o Brasil. Por conta de uma parceria com a Make Wonder, a Happy Code utiliza os robôs Dash &amp; Dot. Além de tornarem as aulas mais divertidas, fazem com que os alunos aprendam a programar através de jogos e projetos. \",\"Para melhor aproveitamento das aulas, as turmas são divididas em três diferentes grupos: Kids (6 a 9 anos), Teens (10 a 14 anos) e Youth (15 a 17 anos). \",\"Para especialistas, o ensino de programação deve ser valorizado assim como nos países desenvolvidos que já implantaram o curso no currículo escolar dos alunos. O aprendizado garante o desenvolvimento do raciocínio lógico, analítico, auxilia na tomada de decisões e ajuda em outras matérias na área de exatas. \",\"Inauguração da sede Happy Code\",\"A Happy Code inaugura a sua sede em Campinas, SP, com capacidade para mais de 2.000 alunos. No dia 23 será a abertura para visitação, esta unidade será o Show Room e também, o centro de formação de novos professores. \",\"Os interessados podem agendar uma aula demonstrativa para conhecer mais a escola e o plano de ensino. \",\"A Happy Code ainda traz uma oportunidade para aqueles que fizerem a matrícula até o dia 27/11: ganharão 50% de desconto na primeira mensalidade, além do convite VIP para a inauguração que será realizada no dia 28/11, que contará com a presença do ícone do Minecraft: o Youtuber Rezendeevil.\",\"Valinhos\",\"Avenida Invernada, 1653, Pq. Nova Suíça - Valinhos - SPContato: (19) 3849-2904/ (19) 98439-4128valinhos@happycode.com.brSegunda: Segunda à Sábado: 09 às 18h00\",\"Campinas\",\"Avenida Dr. Jesuíno Marcondes Machado, 2.400, Chácara da Barra - Campinas - SPContato: (19) 3365-3706/ (19) 98439-4128campinas@happycode.com.br\",\"FONTE  Happy Code\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:10','2015-11-24 17:59:10',NULL),(11464,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/may-your-days-be-merry-and-brightand-may-all-your-energy-bills-be-light-300184014.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:40:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:40:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/may-your-days-be-merry-and-brightand-may-all-your-energy-bills-be-light-300184014.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/may-your-days-be-merry-and-brightand-may-all-your-energy-bills-be-light-300184014.html\"],\"description\":\"CHARLOTTE, N.C., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;The lights and sights of the holiday season make everything merry and bright. \\n\\n\\nTo help customers plan and manage their displays, Duke Energy offers a holiday lighting energy calculator that estimates holiday lighting costs:&#160;www.duke-energy.c\",\"content\":\"CHARLOTTE, N.C., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --&#160;The lights and sights of the holiday season make everything merry and bright. \\n\\n\\nTo help customers plan and manage their displays, Duke Energy offers a holiday lighting energy calculator that estimates holiday lighting costs:&#160;www.duke-energy.c\",\"title\":\"May your days be merry and bright...and may all your energy bills be light\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"CHARLOTTE, N.C., Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The lights and sights of the holiday season make everything merry and bright. \",\"To help customers plan and manage their displays, Duke Energy offers a holiday lighting energy calculator that estimates holiday lighting costs: www.duke-energy.com/lightscalculator.\",\"\\\"An easy way to save money during the holidays is to estimate your energy costs before decorating to incorporate budget-friendly lighting options,\\\" said Sasha Weintraub, Duke Energy senior vice president of customer solutions. \\\"That way you can still dazzle your friends and neighbors with your holiday decorations and save energy and money.\\\"\",\"Users can identify the type of lights, the number of 100-bulb strands and how many hours the lights will be used per day to estimate the energy cost per day and per month. Based on their selections, customers can receive energy-efficient tips and options.\",\"For example, six 100-bulb sets of large, incandescent bulbs (600 bulbs total) plugged in six hours every evening can add as much as $80 to a monthly power bill.\",\"By comparison, six 100-bulb sets of similarly styled light-emitting diode (LED) bulbs would increase a monthly power bill by only about $7. Using six 100-bulb sets of mini-LED bulbs would increase a monthly power bill by only $1.\",\"Other cold weather money-saving tips include:\",\"Safety Tips\",\"For more tips and information on how to save energy and money visit www.duke-energy.com.\",\"About Duke Energy Duke Energy is the largest electric power holding company in the United States. Its regulated utility operations serve approximately 7.3 million electric customers located in six states in the Southeast and Midwest, representing a population of approximately 23 million people. Its Commercial Portfolio and International business segments own and operate diverse power generation assets in North America and Latin America, including a growing portfolio of renewable energy assets in the United States. \",\"Headquartered in Charlotte, N.C., Duke Energy is a Fortune 250 company traded on the New York Stock Exchange under the symbol DUK. More information about the company is available at duke-energy.com.  \",\"Follow Duke Energy on Twitter, LinkedIn and Facebook.\",\"Media Contact:  24-Hour: 800.559.3853 \",\"Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20130322/CL81938LOGO  \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:12','2015-11-24 17:59:12',NULL),(11465,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/analyzing-the-global-market-for-wind-turbine-generators-300184016.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:42:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:42:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/analyzing-the-global-market-for-wind-turbine-generators-300184016.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/analyzing-the-global-market-for-wind-turbine-generators-300184016.html\"],\"description\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The wind turbine generator or WTG is responsible for converting the mechanical energy into electrical energy in a wind turbine. The wind turbine generator works in combination with the power source of the wind turbine that is the wind turbine rotor. There are \",\"content\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The wind turbine generator or WTG is responsible for converting the mechanical energy into electrical energy in a wind turbine. The wind turbine generator works in combination with the power source of the wind turbine that is the wind turbine rotor. There are \",\"title\":\"Analyzing the Global Market for Wind Turbine Generators\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The wind turbine generator or WTG is responsible for converting the mechanical energy into electrical energy in a wind turbine. The wind turbine generator works in combination with the power source of the wind turbine that is the wind turbine rotor. There are many different types of generators that can be used in a wind turbine. However, at the moment, three major types are generally used. These are the induction generator, permanent magnet alternators or Permanent Magnet Synchronous Generators (PMSG) and brushed DC motor. Brushed DC motors are usually put into use in home built wind turbines. The global market for wind turbine generators has always been growing at a good rate with production primarily being concentrated in the regions of Europe and Asia Pacific. Some of the leading manufacturers of wind turbine generators in the global market include ABB, Siemens, Elin, Enercon, Gamesa and others.Aruvian Research analyzes the global market for wind turbine generators in its research offering Analyzing the Global Market for Wind Turbine Generators. The report is a comprehensive coverage of the industry starting from the year 2006 till 2020. Divided into 5 sections, the report begins with an analysis of the global wind power industry and provides an analysis of what is the situation like in the global wind energy market. Beginning with an analysis of the wind power technology and an analysis of market statistics in the global wind energy industry, the industry is analyzed through the regions of Africa and the Middle East, Asia, Europe, North America, South &amp; Latin America, and the Pacific Region. Wind power in the European Union is also analyzed along with a profile of the global offshore wind market.Section 2 of the report analyzes the global wind turbine industry and looks at global installation statistics of wind turbines, market size, cost of turbines and other factors.Section 3 is the main section analyzing the global market for wind turbine generators. Beginning with an overview of what are wind turbine generators, we also analyze the various types of generators available for use in wind turbines. The market for wind turbine generators is analyzed through industry statistics, production statistics, industry size and cost analysis of wind turbine generators.Industry trends and competitive landscape of the sector is also looked at in this report.An analysis of the major industry players involved in the manufacturing of wind turbine generators such as ABB Ltd, China Ming Yang Wind Power Group, Enercon, Siemens, ELIN Motoren, Leroy-Somer Holding, and others is included in the report. Each player is analyzed through a corporate profile/snapshot, a business segment analysis, a financial analysis and a SWOT analysis.Read the full report: http://www.reportlinker.com/p03411185-summary/view-report.htmlAbout Reportlinker ReportLinker is an award-winning market research solution. Reportlinker finds and organizes the latest industry data so you get all the market research you need - instantly, in one place.http://www.reportlinker.com\",\"__________________________Contact Clare: clare@reportlinker.com US: (339)-368-6001Intl: +1 339-368-6001\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:13','2015-11-24 17:59:13',NULL),(11466,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/dassault-delivers-state-of-the-art-medevac-falcon-to-beijing-red-cross-553185481.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:41:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:41:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/dassault-delivers-state-of-the-art-medevac-falcon-to-beijing-red-cross-553185481.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/dassault-delivers-state-of-the-art-medevac-falcon-to-beijing-red-cross-553185481.html\"],\"description\":\"WILMINGTON, Delaware, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nDassault Aviation delivered yesterday a fully outfitted Falcon 2000LX Medevac aircraft to the Beijing Red Cross Emergency Medical Center (999).\\n\\n&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; (Photo: http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151124/776324-a )\\n\\n\\n&#160;&#1\",\"content\":\"WILMINGTON, Delaware, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nDassault Aviation delivered yesterday a fully outfitted Falcon 2000LX Medevac aircraft to the Beijing Red Cross Emergency Medical Center (999).\\n\\n&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160; (Photo: http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151124/776324-a )\\n\\n\\n&#160;&#1\",\"title\":\"Dassault Delivers State-of-the-Art Medevac Falcon to Beijing Red Cross\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"WILMINGTON, Delaware, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\",\"The Falcon 2000LX Medevac aircraft is equipped with an electrical patient loading system and a full medical suite, along with an electrical power supply sized for a complete medical module. The medical module includes a stretcher with dedicated lighting, a three-bottle oxygen supply, and monitoring and analysis equipment. It is also able to accommodate special devices like defibrillators, electrocardiographs, echographs, a blood bank and an ECMO (Extracorporeal membrane oxygenation).\",\"Beijing Red Cross Emergency Medical Center, commonly known as 999, is an International Red Cross Association dedicated to providing critical pre-hospital medical services and has been among the pioneers in the Chinese air ambulance field. Equipped with state of the art medical equipment, including a full digital command center, and staffed by more than 100 medical professionals, 999 was the first air medevac provider in China to launch a three-dimensional rescue package combining ambulances, helicopters and fixed-wing aircraft. In the decade it has been in operation, it has provided pre-hospital rescue and medical treatment service for over 3 million patients.\",\"The combination of long range performance and exceptional airport flexibility make the 4,000 nm Falcon 2000LX perfectly suited to the 999 mission.\",\"The LX and its short field sister aircraft, the Falcon LXS and S, are the latest of seven different Falcon 2000 models that have come off the assembly line since the big twin was introduced two decades ago. And despite its long pedigree, the 2000 remains the most popular business jet in its segment, with more than 550 units currently in service around the world.\",\"Notes for Editors   \",\"Dassault Falcon is the recognized global brand for Dassault business jets which are designed, manufactured and supported by Dassault Aviation and Dassault Falcon Jet Corp.\",\"About Dassault Aviation \",\"Dassault Aviation is a leading aerospace company with a presence in over 90 countries across five continents. It produces the Rafale fighter jet as well as the complete line of Falcons. The company employs a workforce of over 11,000 and has assembly and production plants in both France and the United States and service facilities around the globe. Since the rollout of the first Falcon 20 in 1963, over 2,380 Falcon jets have been delivered. Dassault offers a range of six business jets from the twin-engine 3,350 nm large-cabin Falcon 2000S to its new flagship, the tri-engine 6,450 nm ultra-long range Falcon 8X.\",\"About Dassault Falcon Jet \",\"Dassault Falcon Jet Corp. is a wholly owned U.S. subsidiary of Dassault Aviation, France. Dassault Falcon Jet markets and supports the Falcon family of business jets throughout North and South America.\",\"Photos   \",\"Copy and paste the link into your browser to access the high resolution photos: http://www.falconphotogallery.com\",\"For more information about Dassault Falcon business jets, visit: http://www.dassaultfalcon.com\",\"\\nPress Contacts\",\"Dassault Aviation (Saint-Cloud, France)\\nVadim Feldzer Tel. +33-1-47-11-44-13\\nvadim.feldzer@dassault-aviation.com\\n\\nMarie-Alexandrine Fouillard Tel. +33-1-47-11-64-23\\nmarie-alexandrine.fouillard@dassault-aviation.com\\n\\nDassault Falcon Jet (Teterboro Airport, USA)\\nAndrew Ponzoni Tel. +1-201-541-45-88\\nandrew.ponzoni@falconjet.com\\n\\nGrant Kielczewski Tel. +1-201-541-46-79\\ngrant.kielczewski@falconjet.com\\n\",\"Follow us on Twitter: @DassaultFalcon\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:15','2015-11-24 17:59:15',NULL),(11467,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/av-comparatives-certified-as-first-eicar-trusted-it-security-testing-lab-553185711.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:43:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:43:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/av-comparatives-certified-as-first-eicar-trusted-it-security-testing-lab-553185711.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/av-comparatives-certified-as-first-eicar-trusted-it-security-testing-lab-553185711.html\"],\"description\":\"INNSBRUCK, Austria and MUNICH, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nThe European Expert Group for IT-Security (EICAR) has,  as part of its initiative EICAR Minimum Standards, certified the first IT-security testing lab. AV-Comparatives (http://www.av-comparatives.org ), based in Austria, satisfies  al\",\"content\":\"INNSBRUCK, Austria and MUNICH, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nThe European Expert Group for IT-Security (EICAR) has,  as part of its initiative EICAR Minimum Standards, certified the first IT-security testing lab. AV-Comparatives (http://www.av-comparatives.org ), based in Austria, satisfies  al\",\"title\":\"AV-Comparatives Certified as First EICAR-Trusted IT-Security Testing-Lab\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"INNSBRUCK, Austria and MUNICH, November 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\",\"The European Expert Group for IT-Security (EICAR) has,  as part of its initiative EICAR Minimum Standards, certified the first IT-security testing lab. AV-Comparatives (http://www.av-comparatives.org ), based in Austria, satisfies  all of EICAR\'s standards. \",\"EICAR\'s strategy targets improved transparency in today\'s IT-security environment, with its constantly evolving threats and vulnerabilities, and so aims to increase trust in the available security products.\",\"     (Photo: http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151124/290670 )\\n\",\"Why are minimum standards required for AV testing labs? \",\"AV testing labs gain a deep understanding of the functionality of the products they test. This means they acquire a high level of responsibility for the handling of computer viruses and other malicious programs, as well as for the analysis and presentation of the test results they obtain.\",\"An AV testing lab certified by EICAR demonstrates that it upholds the requirements of the EICAR Minimum Standard.\",\"\\\"Having achieved ISO certification, we are now very pleased to be the first IT-security lab to have  implemented the EICAR Standard with our tests\\\", commented Andreas Clementi, CEO of AV-Comparatives.  \\\"As a lab that works very closely with the University of Innsbruck in the area of science and technology, we are delighted to have another highly valued partner in the form of the EICAR expert group.\\\" \",\"Including testing labs in the initiative is very important to EICAR. Co-operation with certified labs removes doubt from the testing procedure by ensuring that specified standards are maintained for all tested products, and that results can be verified with product manufacturers on a basis of trust.\",\"Additionally, the certification ensures responsible handling of viral code by the testing institute, and that any customer data involved is handled in accordance with data-protection regulations.\",\"\\\"The certification of testing labs is very important to us\\\", said Rainer Fahs, Chairman  of EICAR.  \\\"We know that we can rely 100% on certified testers, and that their tests are carried out in  complete  accordance with our standards\\\". \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 17:59:16','2015-11-24 17:59:16',NULL),(11468,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/fxdd-global-to-offer-clients-complimentary-access-to-fx-navigator-powered-by-tradermade-300184006.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:35:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:35:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/fxdd-global-to-offer-clients-complimentary-access-to-fx-navigator-powered-by-tradermade-300184006.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/fxdd-global-to-offer-clients-complimentary-access-to-fx-navigator-powered-by-tradermade-300184006.html\"],\"description\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- FXDD Global (www.fxdd.com), a leader in online foreign exchange trading, is offering active account holders free access to FX Navigator powered by TraderMade, an institutional-grade analytical tool for foreign exchange traders in effort to further enhance over\",\"content\":\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- FXDD Global (www.fxdd.com), a leader in online foreign exchange trading, is offering active account holders free access to FX Navigator powered by TraderMade, an institutional-grade analytical tool for foreign exchange traders in effort to further enhance over\",\"title\":\"FXDD Global to Offer Clients Complimentary Access to FX Navigator Powered by TraderMade\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"NEW YORK, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- FXDD Global (www.fxdd.com), a leader in online foreign exchange trading, is offering active account holders free access to FX Navigator powered by TraderMade, an institutional-grade analytical tool for foreign exchange traders in effort to further enhance overall trading and user experience. \",\"FX Navigator powered by TraderMade is a subscription-based charting tool and technical analysis workstation used by large asset managers and central banks. With this offer, FXDD Global\'s self-directed and institutional clients will get all of the technology\'s functionality free of charge, including:  \",\"\\\"We are always looking for opportunities to make strategic investments that enable us to provide FXDD Global\'s clients with world-class trading and investment technologies,\\\" said Emil Assentato, chairman and chief executive officer at Currency Mountain Holdings, owner of FXDD Global. \\\"This offering is part of our enduring commitment to put our clients first in everything we do.\\\" \",\"The data provided through FX Navigator is made available through TraderMade, an independent provider of FX data and analytics. Traders and clients have relied on TraderMade for unbiased verification of FX data and pricing for more than 40 years.\",\"About FXDDGlobal FXDD Global (www.fxdd.com) is a global foreign exchange (forex) dealer and subsidiary of Currency Mountain Holdings (www.currencymountain.com). FXDD Global delivers innovative technologies and education that help empower client trading. FXDD Global provides services to individual and institutional traders, hedge funds, commercial entities, brokerage firms and money managers outside of the US. FXDD Global offers a comprehensive array of trading tools and platforms to accommodate all strategies, with dedicated, 24-hour customer service for every account holder. FXDD Global is headquartered in Malta, and is regulated by the Malta Financial Services Authority (MFSA).For more information on FXDD, please visit www.fxdd.com.\",\"Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151123/290250LOGO \"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 18:00:05','2015-11-24 18:00:05',NULL),(11469,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/ibackpack-planning-kickstarter-launch-on-blackfriday-300183934.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-24 12:40:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Tue, 24 Nov 2015 12:40:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/ibackpack-planning-kickstarter-launch-on-blackfriday-300183934.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/ibackpack-planning-kickstarter-launch-on-blackfriday-300183934.html\"],\"description\":\"AUSTIN, Texas, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The iBackPack is a revolutionary new piece of technology encompassed in a normal backpack. Austin, Texas based iBackPack has incorporated WiFi/MiFi capabilities such that anyone carrying the backpack has instant high-speed internet access. Their 20,000 mA\",\"content\":\"AUSTIN, Texas, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The iBackPack is a revolutionary new piece of technology encompassed in a normal backpack. Austin, Texas based iBackPack has incorporated WiFi/MiFi capabilities such that anyone carrying the backpack has instant high-speed internet access. Their 20,000 mA\",\"title\":\"iBackPack Planning Kickstarter Launch on BlackFriday\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"AUSTIN, Texas, Nov. 24, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- The iBackPack is a revolutionary new piece of technology encompassed in a normal backpack. Austin, Texas based iBackPack has incorporated WiFi/MiFi capabilities such that anyone carrying the backpack has instant high-speed internet access. Their 20,000 mAh main battery system is capable of recharging any smartphone up to 10 x from scratch, as well as recharge tablets such as the iPad up to 3 fold. The battery systems allow for wireless recharging of the Apple 5, 6 and 6 Plug by merely placing the iBackPack in close proximity of the battery system. Cables used to transfer power are the latest on the market - called smart cables which display a blue hue when completely charged or a red while charging. Car charging systems are included.\",\"Logo - http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151124/290604LOGO\",\"The WiFi connection is available by piggy-backing on existing carrier subscriptions through AT&amp;T, Verizon, Sprint and T-Mobile. While the exact costs for high-speed internet access for the iBackPack remains the responsibility of the mobile carriers - it is estimated to be approximately ten dollars per month. There is an anti-theft system that utilizes GPS technology to automatically inform someone their iBackPack product has been stolen. Android and iOS mobile apps provide autonomous and full-control over all features of the bag. There is a Bluetooth Speaker that provides high-quality audio listening as well as enables individuals to speak through their iBackPack microphones vs. holding same.\",\"The backpack itself is filled with over fifty high-tech pockets to store multiple iPhones, Androids, iPads and Android tablets. It can carry up to 4 notebook computers and all of the associated cables and plugs. There is a retractable power-cord, similar to those found in vacuum cleaners, that allows for the easy recharge of the iBackPack primary 20,000 mAh battery and auxiliary 8,000 mAh battery banks.\",\"Doug Monahan, CEO &amp; Founder, iBackPack of Texas, Inc. states \\\"Our new backpack is revolutionary in a great many ways. It provides a communication hub and corresponding electrical powerhouse for students and business professionals alike.\\\" Ile Jugovski, Vice President of Operations further reinforces Mr. Monahan\'s claim by exclaiming \\\" Over ten man-years worth of effort have been invested in the WiFi and battery components alone.\\\"\",\"Users will be able to pledge to purchase and support the project through KickStarter within the next few days. www.kickstarter.com The iBackPack is available in two versions - $169 and $219 - the difference in price due to whether someone chooses the WiFi/MiFi option.  Those wishing to receive early bird discounts and VIP access to the development process can visit www.ibackpack.co\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-24 18:00:07','2015-11-24 18:00:07',NULL),(11470,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\