ished\":\"2015-11-25 21:54:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Wed, 25 Nov 2015 21:54:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/sonata-e-ibis-inc-muestran-sus-tecnologias-digital-transformation-en-convergence-2015-emea-554226621.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/sonata-e-ibis-inc-muestran-sus-tecnologias-digital-transformation-en-convergence-2015-emea-554226621.html\"],\"description\":\"BANGALORE, November 26, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nSonata Software, una compa&#241;&#237;a de servicios y soluciones de tecnolog&#237;a global, y su filial recientemente adquirida I.B.I.S., Inc. (INTERACTIVE BUSINESS INFORMATION SYSTEMS, INC.), un proveedor de software y servicios de la cadena de suminis\",\"content\":\"BANGALORE, November 26, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\\n\\nSonata Software, una compa&#241;&#237;a de servicios y soluciones de tecnolog&#237;a global, y su filial recientemente adquirida I.B.I.S., Inc. (INTERACTIVE BUSINESS INFORMATION SYSTEMS, INC.), un proveedor de software y servicios de la cadena de suminis\",\"title\":\"Sonata e I.B.I.S., Inc muestran sus tecnologías Digital Transformation en Convergence 2015 EMEA\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"BANGALORE, November 26, 2015 /PRNewswire/ --\",\"Sonata Software, una compañía de servicios y soluciones de tecnología global, y su filial recientemente adquirida I.B.I.S., Inc. (INTERACTIVE BUSINESS INFORMATION SYSTEMS, INC.), un proveedor de software y servicios de la cadena de suministro y un Microsoft Dynamics® strategic Partner; anunciaron hoy que mostrarán conjuntamente sus tecnologías Digital Transformation en la Convergence 2015 EMEA que se celebrará en Barcelona (España) entre el 30 de noviembre y el 2 de diciembre de 2015.\",\"     (Logo: http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20130610/618887)\\n\",\"     (Logo: http://photos.prnewswire.com/prnh/20151125/778576)\\n\",\"Durante el evento, Sonata mostrará sus plataformas y soluciones empresariales digitales, como comercio minorista Brick &amp; Click, una plataforma del futuro para obtener lo mejor del comercio minorista en tienda y digital, impulsar una experiencia del cliente superior y ganar en la nueva economía. I.B.I.S., Inc. mostrará sus soluciones de la cadena de suministro Microsoft Dynamics® AX y CRM - Advanced Supply Chain Software™, diseñado para cubrir las necesidades de los distribuidores, fabricantes y minoristas modernos. Una combinación ganadora de experiencia en la cadena de suministro de la industria, el software de la cadena de suministro de clase mundial y 26 años de implementaciones de éxito de Microsoft Dynamics®, ha culminado en convertir a I.B.I.S. en el Microsoft Dynamics® Partner preferente y proveedor de soluciones para distribuidores y fabricantes en todo el mundo.\",\"La experiencia, propiedad intelectual, escala y presencia global de Sonata con Microsoft Dynamics® AX, especialmente en la industria minorista, junto con la experiencia de I.B.I.S., IP y fuerte huella local en EE. UU. dentro del espacio de la industria de distribución mostrarán la potente oferta de estas entidades combinadas para una transformación digital, cubriendo a compañías de comercio minorista, CPG y distribución globalmente que deseen desplegar Microsoft Dynamics®.\",\"En esta ocasión, PVSN Raju, responsable, Delivery, Sonata Software, dijo: \\\"La transformación digital de éxito no solo surge de implementar nuevas tecnologías sino de transformar su organización para aprovechar las posibilidades. La fuerte asociación de Sonata con Microsoft on Dynamics globalmente, junto con I.B.I.S. Inc., aporta capacidades complementarias para hacer que estas posibilidades se hagan realidad para nuestros clientes destacados\\\".\",\"Andy Vabulas, fundador y consejero delegado de I.B.I.S., Inc. comentó: \\\"Sonata y I.B.I.S. están encantadas de formar parte de Convergence 2015 EMEA. Es una fantástica plataforma donde las empresas se encuentran con las posibilidades. Nuestras capacidades combinadas van a inspirar con seguridad a las organizaciones para impulsar el éxito y la innovación dentro de sus empresas, beneficiándose de la profundidad y amplitud de los productos y servicios que ponemos sobre la mesa\\\".\",\"Para saber más sobre nuestras ofertas, visítenos en el expositor # 82 y 111.\",\"Microsoft Convergence es el principal evento para la comunidad empresarial de Microsoft. Microsoft Convergence es el sitio donde los líderes se reúnen para explorar, compartir y experimentar soluciones empresariales, ver las últimas innovaciones, obtener perspectivas y opiniones, entrar en contacto con expertos y homólogos y replantear el negocio. El registro anterior muestra que 78 países estuvieron representados en Convergence 2014 EMEA, Barcelona, atrajeron a más de 4.000 personas, incluyendo delegados, prensa, ponentes y personal. Este año los asistentes serán clientes de Microsoft, clientes prospectivos, socios y prensa/análisis.\",\"Acerca de Sonata Software  \",\"Sonata Software es una firma de servicios TI global centrada en catalizar iniciativas TI transformacionales de sus clientes mediante un conocimiento de dominio profundo, experiencia en tecnología y compromiso con el cliente. La compañía ofrece nuevas e innovadoras soluciones para viaje, comercio minorista y productos de consumo y compañías de productos de software integrando tecnologías como comercio omni-canal, movilidad, análisis, nube y ERP, para impulsar la implicación del cliente, la eficiencia de las operaciones y el retorno de las inversiones en TI. Un proveedor de servicios a largo plazo para las compañías Fortune 500 en los segmentos de desarrollo de productos de software y empresarial, Sonata busca añadir un valor diferenciado a los directivos que deseen tener un impacto en sus empresas, con la TI.\",\"Acerca de I.B.I.S., Inc.  \",\"Fundada en 1989, I.B.I.S., Inc. ofrece soluciones empresariales que permiten a las compañías con requisitos de la cadena de suministro complejos maximizar su éxito empresarial. Mediante una relación Strategic Developer Partner con Microsoft, la compañía ofrece soluciones de clase mundial para planificación de recursos empresariales (ERP), gestión de relaciones con el cliente (CRM), inteligencia empresarial (BI) y desarrollo de aplicaciones. Las especialidades de I.B.I.S., Inc. incluyen soluciones de Microsoft Dynamics® AX y CRM centradas en las necesidades de la cadena de suministro de las industrias de distribución, fabricación y comercio minorista.\",\"I.B.I.S., Inc. es dos veces ganador del Microsoft Dynamics® Outstanding Partner of the United States Award, finalista mundial del Microsoft Dynamics® AX Partner of the Year, Microsoft Dynamics® 2015 Distribution Partner of the Year en EE. UU., Microsoft Partner con Four Gold Competencies (ERP, CRM, Business Intelligence, Application Development), y diez veces ganador del Microsoft Dynamics® Inner Circle Partner. Además, I.B.I.S., Inc. se encuentra entre las pocas compañías selectas que son Microsoft Dynamics Global Independent Software Vendors para Dynamics AX y CRM.\",\"Para más información, contacte con:\\nAnuj Kumar Saxena\\nSonata Software Limited\\nCIN- L72200MH1994PLC082110\\nA.P.S. Trust Building,\\nBull Temple Road, N.R. Colonia\\nBangalore 560019, India\\nTel: +91 80 67781999\\nanujkumar.s@sonata-software.com\\nSitio web: http://www.sonata-software.com\\n\"],\"answers\":[{\"deal\":\"yes\",\"feedback\":\"Type here...\"}]}','2015-11-26 03:23:20','2015-11-26 03:23:20',NULL),(11886,1,8,NULL,NULL,'{\"id\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/morningstar-canada-announces-winners-of-2015-morningstar-awards-300184796.html\",\"date_published\":\"2015-11-25 22:05:00 -0500\",\"last_updated\":\"Wed, 25 Nov 2015 22:05:00 -0500\",\"url\":\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/morningstar-canada-announces-winners-of-2015-morningstar-awards-300184796.html\",\"urls\":[\"http://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/morningstar-canada-announces-winners-of-2015-morningstar-awards-300184796.html\"],\"description\":\"TORONTO, Nov. 25, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Morningstar Research, Inc., a Canadian subsidiary of Morningstar, Inc. (NASDAQ: MORN), a leading provider of independent investment research, today announced the winners of the 2015 Morningstar Awards. The Morningstar Awards are designed to help investors ident\",\"content\":\"TORONTO, Nov. 25, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Morningstar Research, Inc., a Canadian subsidiary of Morningstar, Inc. (NASDAQ: MORN), a leading provider of independent investment research, today announced the winners of the 2015 Morningstar Awards. The Morningstar Awards are designed to help investors ident\",\"title\":\"Morningstar Canada Announces Winners of 2015 Morningstar Awards\",\"authors\":[],\"categories\":[],\"copy\":[\"TORONTO, Nov. 25, 2015 /PRNewswire/ -- Morningstar Research, Inc., a Canadian subsidiary of Morningstar, Inc. (NASDAQ:  MORN), a leading provider of independent investment research, today announced the winners of the 2015 Morningstar Awards. The Morningstar Awards are designed to help investors identify the country\'s most exceptional funds and fund managers of the year. Morningstar hosted the 21st annual Awards gala, at the Fairmont Royal York Hotel in Toronto, honouring more than 40 individuals and companies that Morningstar believes have made a difference in the lives of investors.  \",\"The awards encompass a wide range of investment products, including mutual funds and pooled funds. Additional awards recognize outstanding individual managers, online brokerages, investor education, and marketing campaigns. The awards program represents an extensive, year-long evaluation of dozens of firms and industry individuals by analysts and experienced jury members.\",\"Morningstar introduced two new awards this year. The new Breakout Fund Manager of the Year award recognizes up-and-coming managers worthy of investors\' attention. The Morningstar Multi-Asset Fund Manager of the Year award acknowledges managers who have invested successfully across asset classes.\",\"Ed Robertson, lead singer, songwriter, and a founding member of Barenaked Ladies, was the host and emcee to more than 500 guests in attendance. \",\"The 2015 Morningstar Awards winners are:\",\"Fund Manager of the Year Awards:\",\"Morningstar Domestic Equity Fund Manager of the YearWinner: Jim Hall and Vijay Viswanathan, Mawer Canadian Equity, Mawer Investment Management Ltd. Finalists: Tye Bousada and Geoff MacDonald, EdgePoint Canadian Portfolio, EdgePoint Wealth Management Inc.Maxime Lemieux, Fidelity True North, Fidelity Investments Canada ULC\",\"\\\"Managers Jim Hall and Vijay Viswanathan benefited from their historical aversion to energy and basic materials stocks,\\\" Christopher Davis, director of manager research for Morningstar Canada, said. \\\"Their focus on high-quality investments and big winners like Constellation Software kept their fund comfortably in the black as most of their peers suffered losses. Their long-term risk-adjusted performance is extraordinary.\\\" \",\"Morningstar Foreign Equity Fund Manager of the YearWinner: Richard Jenkins, CI Black Creek International Equity, CI Investments Inc.Finalists: Carl Kawaja, Dina Perry, and Galen Hoskin, Capital Group Global Equity—Canada, Capital International Asset Management (Canada), Inc.Paul Moroz, Mawer Global Small Cap, Mawer Investment Management Ltd. \",\"\\\"Richard Jenkins pushed ahead of the pack by investing differently than the competition,\\\" Davis said. \\\"Picks like brick maker Weinerberger and packaging producer Gerresheimer don\'t appear in many rival portfolios. The success of names like these led to terrific performance this year, and more importantly, over the long term.\\\" \",\"Morningstar Fixed-Income Fund Manager of the YearWinner: Daniel Janis, Thomas Goggins, and Kisoo Park, Manulife Strategic Income, Manulife Asset Management Ltd.Finalist: Stephen Burke, PH&amp;N Bond and PH&amp;N Total Return Bond, RBC Global Asset Management Inc.\",\"\\\"Dan Janis, Thomas Goggins, and Kisoo Park got some big calls right,\\\" Davis said. \\\"They gave their portfolio a conservative bent and positioned it for Canadian dollar weakness–moves that paid off nicely this year. Savvy decisions like these are nothing new for the team, explaining their success over the long haul.\\\" \",\"Morningstar Multi-Asset Fund Manager of the Year  Winner: Geoffrey Stein and David Wolf, Fidelity Global Monthly Income, Fidelity Canadian Asset Allocation, and Fidelity Monthly Income, Fidelity Investments Canada ULC Finalists: Tye Bousada, Geoff MacDonald, and Frank Mullen, EdgePoint Canadian Growth &amp; Income Portfolio and EdgePoint Global Growth &amp; Income Portfolio, EdgePoint Wealth Management Inc.Alan Wicks, Conrad Dabiet, and Jonathan Popper, Manulife Monthly High Income Fund, Manulife Asset Management Ltd.\",\"\\\"Managers Geoffrey Stein and David Wolf show you don\'t need to make flashy asset allocation shifts to succeed,\\\" says Davis said. \\\"They modestly tilted their portfolios toward US equities and bonds, for example, which helped them beat their peers. While their asset allocation has been a positive, their funds have also benefited from strong performance of their stock and bond holdings alike.\\\"\",\"Morningstar Analysts\' Choice Steward of the Year: EdgePoint Wealth Management, Inc. \",\"\\\"EdgePoint built top-rate stewardship practices into its DNA right from the beginning,\\\" Davis said. \\\"The firm kept its lineup simple, avoided expensive marketing to keep costs low, and committed to close funds at conservative asset levels. Heavy co-investment from EdgePoint managers assures alignment with fund holder interests.\\\"\",\"Breakout Fund Manager of the Year: Winner:  Stephen Groff and Greg Dean, CI Cambridge Pure Canadian Equity Fund, CI Investments Inc.Finalists:Ken O\'Kennedy, Pender Canadian Equity, Dixon Mitchell Investment Counsel Geoff Marshall, CI Signature High Yield, CI Investments Inc.\",\"Advisors\' Choice Investment Fund Company of the Year:  Winner: Fidelity Investments Canada ULC Finalists:  OceanRock Investments Inc.CI Investments Inc.\",\"Career Achievement: Winner: Philip Armstrong   \",\"Mutual Fund Awards:\",\"Best Canadian Balanced FundWinner: Manulife Monthly High Income, Manulife Asset Management Ltd.Finalists: EdgePoint Canadian Growth &amp; Income, EdgePoint Wealth Management Inc.Fidelity Canadian Balanced, Fidelity Investments Canada ULC \",\"Best Canadian Dividend &amp; Income Equity FundWinner: Manulife Dividend Income, Manulife Asset Management Ltd.Finalists:Beutel Goodman Canadian Dividend, Beutel, Goodman &amp; Company Ltd. Fidelity Dividend, Fidelity Investments Canada ULC\",\"Best Canadian Equity FundWinner: CI Cambridge Canadian Equity, CI Investments Inc.Finalists:Fidelity Canadian Large Cap, Fidelity Investments Canada ULCSteadyhand Equity, Steadyhand Investment Funds Inc.\",\"Best Canadian Fixed-Income FundWinner: PH&amp;N Total Return Bond, RBC Global Asset Management Inc.Finalists:Dynamic Aurion Total Return Bond, Dynamic Funds Fidelity Canadian Bond, Fidelity Investments Canada ULC \",\"Best Canadian Small-/Mid-Cap Equity Fund Winner: Fidelity Special Situations, Fidelity Investments Canada ULCFinalists: Sentry Small/Mid Cap Income, Sentry InvestmentsMawer New Canada, Mawer Investment Management Ltd.\",\"Best Emerging Markets Equity FundWinner: RBC Emerging Markets Equity, RBC Global Asset Management Inc. Finalists: Mackenzie Emerging Markets, Mackenzie InvestmentsRedwood Emerging Markets Dividend Fund, Redwood Asset Management Inc. \",\"Best Fund of Fund SeriesWinner: Fidelity Managed Portfolios, Fidelity Investments Canada ULCFinalists:CI Portfolio Series, CI Investments Inc. CI Portfolio Select, CI Investments Inc.\",\"Best Global Balanced Fund Winner: EdgePoint Global Growth &amp; Income Portfolio, EdgePoint Wealth Management Inc.Finalists: Mawer Balanced, Mawer Investment Management Ltd.Fidelity Global Monthly Inc